95 class IfConverter : public MachineFunctionPass { ----
96 enum IfcvtKind { ----
97 ICNotClassfied, // BB data valid, but not classified. ----
98 ICSimpleFalse, // Same as ICSimple, but on the false path. ----
99 ICSimple, // BB is entry of an one split, no rejoin sub-CFG. ----
100 ICTriangleFRev, // Same as ICTriangleFalse, but false path rev condition. ----
101 ICTriangleRev, // Same as ICTriangle, but true path rev condition. ----
102 ICTriangleFalse, // Same as ICTriangle, but on the false path. ----
103 ICTriangle, // BB is entry of a triangle sub-CFG. ----
104 ICDiamond, // BB is entry of a diamond sub-CFG. ----
105 ICForkedDiamond // BB is entry of an almost diamond sub-CFG, with a ----
106 // common tail that can be shared. ----
107 }; ----
108 ----
109 /// One per MachineBasicBlock, this is used to cache the result ----
110 /// if-conversion feasibility analysis. This includes results from ----
111 /// TargetInstrInfo::analyzeBranch() (i.e. TBB, FBB, and Cond), and its ----
112 /// classification, and common tail block of its successors (if it's a ----
113 /// diamond shape), its size, whether it's predicable, and whether any ----
114 /// instruction can clobber the 'would-be' predicate. ----
115 /// ----
116 /// IsDone - True if BB is not to be considered for ifcvt. ----
117 /// IsBeingAnalyzed - True if BB is currently being analyzed. ----
118 /// IsAnalyzed - True if BB has been analyzed (info is still valid). ----
119 /// IsEnqueued - True if BB has been enqueued to be ifcvt'ed. ----
120 /// IsBrAnalyzable - True if analyzeBranch() returns false. ----
121 /// HasFallThrough - True if BB may fallthrough to the following BB. ----
122 /// IsUnpredicable - True if BB is known to be unpredicable. ----
123 /// ClobbersPred - True if BB could modify predicates (e.g. has ----
124 /// cmp, call, etc.) ----
125 /// NonPredSize - Number of non-predicated instructions. ----
126 /// ExtraCost - Extra cost for multi-cycle instructions. ----
127 /// ExtraCost2 - Some instructions are slower when predicated ----
128 /// BB - Corresponding MachineBasicBlock. ----
129 /// TrueBB / FalseBB- See analyzeBranch(). ----
130 /// BrCond - Conditions for end of block conditional branches. ----
131 /// Predicate - Predicate used in the BB. ----
132 struct BBInfo { ----
133 bool IsDone : 1; ----
134 bool IsBeingAnalyzed : 1; ----
135 bool IsAnalyzed : 1; ----
136 bool IsEnqueued : 1; ----
137 bool IsBrAnalyzable : 1; ----
138 bool IsBrReversible : 1; ----
139 bool HasFallThrough : 1; ----
140 bool IsUnpredicable : 1; ----
141 bool CannotBeCopied : 1; ----
142 bool ClobbersPred : 1; ----
143 unsigned NonPredSize = 0; ----
144 unsigned ExtraCost = 0; ----
145 unsigned ExtraCost2 = 0; ----
146 MachineBasicBlock *BB = nullptr; ----
147 MachineBasicBlock *TrueBB = nullptr; ----
148 MachineBasicBlock *FalseBB = nullptr; ----
149 SmallVector BrCond; ----
150 SmallVector Predicate; ----
151 ----
152 BBInfo() : IsDone(false), IsBeingAnalyzed(false), 0
153 IsAnalyzed(false), IsEnqueued(false), IsBrAnalyzable(false), 0
154 IsBrReversible(false), HasFallThrough(false), 0
155 IsUnpredicable(false), CannotBeCopied(false), 0
156 ClobbersPred(false) {} 0
157 }; ----
158 ----
159 /// Record information about pending if-conversions to attempt: ----
160 /// BBI - Corresponding BBInfo. ----
161 /// Kind - Type of block. See IfcvtKind. ----
162 /// NeedSubsumption - True if the to-be-predicated BB has already been ----
163 /// predicated. ----
164 /// NumDups - Number of instructions that would be duplicated due ----
165 /// to this if-conversion. (For diamonds, the number of ----
166 /// identical instructions at the beginnings of both ----
167 /// paths). ----
168 /// NumDups2 - For diamonds, the number of identical instructions ----
169 /// at the ends of both paths. ----
170 struct IfcvtToken { ----
171 BBInfo &BBI; ----
172 IfcvtKind Kind; ----
173 unsigned NumDups; ----
174 unsigned NumDups2; ----
175 bool NeedSubsumption : 1; ----
176 bool TClobbersPred : 1; ----
177 bool FClobbersPred : 1; ----
178 ----
179 IfcvtToken(BBInfo &b, IfcvtKind k, bool s, unsigned d, unsigned d2 = 0, 0
180 bool tc = false, bool fc = false) ----
181 : BBI(b), Kind(k), NumDups(d), NumDups2(d2), NeedSubsumption(s), 0
182 TClobbersPred(tc), FClobbersPred(fc) {} 0
183 }; ----

282 bool MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(MachineBasicBlock &BB, 0
283 unsigned Cycle, unsigned Extra, ----
284 BranchProbability Prediction) const { ----
285 return Cycle > 0 && TII->isProfitableToIfCvt(BB, Cycle, Extra, 0
286 Prediction); 0
287 } ----
288 ----
289 bool MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(BBInfo &TBBInfo, BBInfo &FBBInfo, 0
290 MachineBasicBlock &CommBB, unsigned Dups, ----
291 BranchProbability Prediction, bool Forked) const { ----
292 const MachineFunction &MF = *TBBInfo.BB->getParent(); 0
293 if (MF.getFunction().hasMinSize()) { 0
294 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIB = TBBInfo.BB->begin(); 0
295 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIB = FBBInfo.BB->begin(); 0
296 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIE = TBBInfo.BB->end(); 0
297 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIE = FBBInfo.BB->end(); 0
298 ----
299 unsigned Dups1 = 0, Dups2 = 0; 0
300 if (!CountDuplicatedInstructions(TIB, FIB, TIE, FIE, Dups1, Dups2, 0
301 *TBBInfo.BB, *FBBInfo.BB, 0
302 /*SkipUnconditionalBranches*/ true)) ----
303 llvm_unreachable("should already have been checked by ValidDiamond"); 0
304 ----
305 unsigned BranchBytes = 0; 0
306 unsigned CommonBytes = 0; 0
307 ----
308 // Count common instructions at the start of the true and false blocks. ----
309 for (auto &I : make_range(TBBInfo.BB->begin(), TIB)) { 0
310 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Common inst: " << I); 0
311 CommonBytes += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(I); 0
312 } ----
313 for (auto &I : make_range(FBBInfo.BB->begin(), FIB)) { 0
314 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Common inst: " << I); 0
315 CommonBytes += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(I); 0
316 } ----
317 ----
318 // Count instructions at the end of the true and false blocks, after ----
319 // the ones we plan to predicate. Analyzable branches will be removed ----
320 // (unless this is a forked diamond), and all other instructions are ----
321 // common between the two blocks. ----
322 for (auto &I : make_range(TIE, TBBInfo.BB->end())) { 0
323 if (I.isBranch() && TBBInfo.IsBrAnalyzable && !Forked) { 0
324 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Saving branch: " << I); 0
325 BranchBytes += TII->predictBranchSizeForIfCvt(I); 0
326 } else { ----
327 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Common inst: " << I); 0
328 CommonBytes += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(I); 0
329 } ----
330 } ----
331 for (auto &I : make_range(FIE, FBBInfo.BB->end())) { 0
332 if (I.isBranch() && FBBInfo.IsBrAnalyzable && !Forked) { 0
333 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Saving branch: " << I); 0
334 BranchBytes += TII->predictBranchSizeForIfCvt(I); 0
335 } else { ----
336 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Common inst: " << I); 0
337 CommonBytes += TII->getInstSizeInBytes(I); 0
338 } ----
339 } ----
340 for (auto &I : CommBB.terminators()) { 0
341 if (I.isBranch()) { 0
342 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Saving branch: " << I); 0
343 BranchBytes += TII->predictBranchSizeForIfCvt(I); 0
344 } ----
345 } ----
346 ----
347 // The common instructions in one branch will be eliminated, halving ----
348 // their code size. ----
349 CommonBytes /= 2; 0
350 ----
351 // Count the instructions which we need to predicate. ----
352 unsigned NumPredicatedInstructions = 0; 0
353 for (auto &I : make_range(TIB, TIE)) { 0
354 if (!I.isDebugInstr()) { 0
355 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Predicating: " << I); 0
356 NumPredicatedInstructions++; 0
357 } ----
358 } ----
359 for (auto &I : make_range(FIB, FIE)) { 0
360 if (!I.isDebugInstr()) { 0
361 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Predicating: " << I); 0
362 NumPredicatedInstructions++; 0
363 } ----
364 } ----
365 ----
366 // Even though we're optimising for size at the expense of performance, ----
367 // avoid creating really long predicated blocks. ----
368 if (NumPredicatedInstructions > 15) 0
369 return false; 0
370 ----
371 // Some targets (e.g. Thumb2) need to insert extra instructions to ----
372 // start predicated blocks. ----
373 unsigned ExtraPredicateBytes = TII->extraSizeToPredicateInstructions( 0
374 MF, NumPredicatedInstructions); ----
375 ----
376 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(BranchBytes=" << BranchBytes 0
377 << ", CommonBytes=" << CommonBytes ----
378 << ", NumPredicatedInstructions=" ----
379 << NumPredicatedInstructions ----
380 << ", ExtraPredicateBytes=" << ExtraPredicateBytes ----
381 << ")\n"); ----
382 return (BranchBytes + CommonBytes) > ExtraPredicateBytes; 0
383 } else { ----
384 unsigned TCycle = TBBInfo.NonPredSize + TBBInfo.ExtraCost - Dups; 0
385 unsigned FCycle = FBBInfo.NonPredSize + FBBInfo.ExtraCost - Dups; 0
386 bool Res = TCycle > 0 && FCycle > 0 && 0
387 TII->isProfitableToIfCvt( 0
388 *TBBInfo.BB, TCycle, TBBInfo.ExtraCost2, *FBBInfo.BB, 0
389 FCycle, FBBInfo.ExtraCost2, Prediction); 0
390 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(TCycle=" << TCycle 0
391 << ", FCycle=" << FCycle ----
392 << ", TExtra=" << TBBInfo.ExtraCost2 << ", FExtra=" ----
393 << FBBInfo.ExtraCost2 << ") = " << Res << "\n"); ----
394 return Res; 0
395 } ----
396 } ----
397 ----
398 /// Returns true if Block ends without a terminator. ----
399 bool blockAlwaysFallThrough(BBInfo &BBI) const { 0
400 return BBI.IsBrAnalyzable && BBI.TrueBB == nullptr; 0
401 } ----
402 ----
403 /// Used to sort if-conversion candidates. ----
404 static bool IfcvtTokenCmp(const std::unique_ptr &C1, 0
405 const std::unique_ptr &C2) { ----
406 int Incr1 = (C1->Kind == ICDiamond) 0
407 ? -(int)(C1->NumDups + C1->NumDups2) : (int)C1->NumDups; 0
408 int Incr2 = (C2->Kind == ICDiamond) 0
409 ? -(int)(C2->NumDups + C2->NumDups2) : (int)C2->NumDups; 0
410 if (Incr1 > Incr2) 0
411 return true; 0
412 else if (Incr1 == Incr2) { 0
413 // Favors subsumption. ----
414 if (!C1->NeedSubsumption && C2->NeedSubsumption) 0
415 return true; 0
416 else if (C1->NeedSubsumption == C2->NeedSubsumption) { 0
417 // Favors diamond over triangle, etc. ----
418 if ((unsigned)C1->Kind < (unsigned)C2->Kind) 0
419 return true; 0
420 else if (C1->Kind == C2->Kind) 0
421 return C1->BBI.BB->getNumber() < C2->BBI.BB->getNumber(); 0
422 } ----
423 } ----
424 return false; 0
425 } ----
426 }; ----

438 ----
439 bool IfConverter::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
440 if (skipFunction(MF.getFunction()) || (PredicateFtor && !PredicateFtor(MF))) 0
441 return false; 0
442 ----
443 const TargetSubtargetInfo &ST = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
444 TLI = ST.getTargetLowering(); 0
445 TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
446 TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
447 MBFIWrapper MBFI(getAnalysis()); 0
448 MBPI = &getAnalysis(); 0
449 ProfileSummaryInfo *PSI = ----
450 &getAnalysis().getPSI(); 0
451 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
452 SchedModel.init(&ST); 0
453 ----
454 if (!TII) return false; 0
455 ----
456 PreRegAlloc = MRI->isSSA(); 0
457 ----
458 bool BFChange = false; 0
459 if (!PreRegAlloc) { 0
460 // Tail merge tend to expose more if-conversion opportunities. ----
461 BranchFolder BF(true, false, MBFI, *MBPI, PSI); 0
462 BFChange = BF.OptimizeFunction(MF, TII, ST.getRegisterInfo()); 0
463 } 0
464 ----
465 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nIfcvt: function (" << ++FnNum << ") \'" 0
466 << MF.getName() << "\'"); ----
467 ----
468 if (FnNum < IfCvtFnStart || (IfCvtFnStop != -1 && FnNum > IfCvtFnStop)) { 0
469 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " skipped\n"); 0
470 return false; 0
471 } ----
472 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\n"); 0
473 ----
474 MF.RenumberBlocks(); 0
475 BBAnalysis.resize(MF.getNumBlockIDs()); 0
476 ----
477 std::vector> Tokens; 0
478 MadeChange = false; 0
479 unsigned NumIfCvts = NumSimple + NumSimpleFalse + NumTriangle + 0
480 NumTriangleRev + NumTriangleFalse + NumTriangleFRev + NumDiamonds; 0
481 while (IfCvtLimit == -1 || (int)NumIfCvts < IfCvtLimit) { 0
482 // Do an initial analysis for each basic block and find all the potential ----
483 // candidates to perform if-conversion. ----
484 bool Change = false; 0
485 AnalyzeBlocks(MF, Tokens); 0
486 while (!Tokens.empty()) { 0
487 std::unique_ptr Token = std::move(Tokens.back()); 0
488 Tokens.pop_back(); 0
489 BBInfo &BBI = Token->BBI; 0
490 IfcvtKind Kind = Token->Kind; 0
491 unsigned NumDups = Token->NumDups; 0
492 unsigned NumDups2 = Token->NumDups2; 0
493 ----
494 // If the block has been evicted out of the queue or it has already been ----
495 // marked dead (due to it being predicated), then skip it. ----
496 if (BBI.IsDone) 0
497 BBI.IsEnqueued = false; 0
498 if (!BBI.IsEnqueued) 0
499 continue; 0
500 ----
501 BBI.IsEnqueued = false; 0
502 ----
503 bool RetVal = false; 0
504 switch (Kind) { 0
505 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected!"); 0
506 case ICSimple: 0
507 case ICSimpleFalse: { ----
508 bool isFalse = Kind == ICSimpleFalse; 0
509 if ((isFalse && DisableSimpleF) || (!isFalse && DisableSimple)) break; 0
510 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Ifcvt (Simple" 0
511 << (Kind == ICSimpleFalse ? " false" : "") ----
512 << "): " << printMBBReference(*BBI.BB) << " (" ----
513 << ((Kind == ICSimpleFalse) ? BBI.FalseBB->getNumber() ----
514 : BBI.TrueBB->getNumber()) ----
515 << ") "); ----
516 RetVal = IfConvertSimple(BBI, Kind); 0
517 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (RetVal ? "succeeded!" : "failed!") << "\n"); 0
518 if (RetVal) { 0
519 if (isFalse) ++NumSimpleFalse; 0
520 else ++NumSimple; 0
521 } ----
522 break; 0
523 } ----
524 case ICTriangle: 0
525 case ICTriangleRev: ----
526 case ICTriangleFalse: ----
527 case ICTriangleFRev: { ----
528 bool isFalse = Kind == ICTriangleFalse; 0
529 bool isRev = (Kind == ICTriangleRev || Kind == ICTriangleFRev); 0
530 if (DisableTriangle && !isFalse && !isRev) break; 0
531 if (DisableTriangleR && !isFalse && isRev) break; 0
532 if (DisableTriangleF && isFalse && !isRev) break; 0
533 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Ifcvt (Triangle"); 0
534 if (isFalse) 0
535 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " false"); 0
536 if (isRev) 0
537 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " rev"); 0
538 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "): " << printMBBReference(*BBI.BB) 0
539 << " (T:" << BBI.TrueBB->getNumber() ----
540 << ",F:" << BBI.FalseBB->getNumber() << ") "); ----
541 RetVal = IfConvertTriangle(BBI, Kind); 0
542 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (RetVal ? "succeeded!" : "failed!") << "\n"); 0
543 if (RetVal) { 0
544 if (isFalse) { 0
545 if (isRev) ++NumTriangleFRev; 0
546 else ++NumTriangleFalse; 0
547 } else { ----
548 if (isRev) ++NumTriangleRev; 0
549 else ++NumTriangle; 0
550 } ----
551 } ----
552 break; 0
553 } ----
554 case ICDiamond: 0
555 if (DisableDiamond) break; 0
556 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Ifcvt (Diamond): " << printMBBReference(*BBI.BB) 0
557 << " (T:" << BBI.TrueBB->getNumber() ----
558 << ",F:" << BBI.FalseBB->getNumber() << ") "); ----
559 RetVal = IfConvertDiamond(BBI, Kind, NumDups, NumDups2, 0
560 Token->TClobbersPred, 0
561 Token->FClobbersPred); 0
562 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (RetVal ? "succeeded!" : "failed!") << "\n"); 0
563 if (RetVal) ++NumDiamonds; 0
564 break; 0
565 case ICForkedDiamond: 0
566 if (DisableForkedDiamond) break; 0
567 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Ifcvt (Forked Diamond): " 0
568 << printMBBReference(*BBI.BB) ----
569 << " (T:" << BBI.TrueBB->getNumber() ----
570 << ",F:" << BBI.FalseBB->getNumber() << ") "); ----
571 RetVal = IfConvertForkedDiamond(BBI, Kind, NumDups, NumDups2, 0
572 Token->TClobbersPred, 0
573 Token->FClobbersPred); 0
574 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (RetVal ? "succeeded!" : "failed!") << "\n"); 0
575 if (RetVal) ++NumForkedDiamonds; 0
576 break; 0
577 } ----
578 ----
579 if (RetVal && MRI->tracksLiveness()) 0
580 recomputeLivenessFlags(*BBI.BB); 0
581 ----
582 Change |= RetVal; 0
583 ----
584 NumIfCvts = NumSimple + NumSimpleFalse + NumTriangle + NumTriangleRev + 0
585 NumTriangleFalse + NumTriangleFRev + NumDiamonds; 0
586 if (IfCvtLimit != -1 && (int)NumIfCvts >= IfCvtLimit) 0
587 break; 0
588 } 0
589 ----
590 if (!Change) 0
591 break; 0
592 MadeChange |= Change; 0
593 } ----
594 ----
595 Tokens.clear(); 0
596 BBAnalysis.clear(); 0
597 ----
598 if (MadeChange && IfCvtBranchFold) { 0
599 BranchFolder BF(false, false, MBFI, *MBPI, PSI); 0
600 BF.OptimizeFunction(MF, TII, MF.getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo()); 0
601 } 0
602 ----
603 MadeChange |= BFChange; 0
604 return MadeChange; 0
605 } 0
606 ----
607 /// BB has a fallthrough. Find its 'false' successor given its 'true' successor. ----
608 static MachineBasicBlock *findFalseBlock(MachineBasicBlock *BB, 0
609 MachineBasicBlock *TrueBB) { ----
610 for (MachineBasicBlock *SuccBB : BB->successors()) { 0
611 if (SuccBB != TrueBB) 0
612 return SuccBB; 0
613 } ----
614 return nullptr; 0
615 } ----
616 ----
617 /// Reverse the condition of the end of the block branch. Swap block's 'true' ----
618 /// and 'false' successors. ----
619 bool IfConverter::reverseBranchCondition(BBInfo &BBI) const { 0
620 DebugLoc dl; // FIXME: this is nowhere 0
621 if (!TII->reverseBranchCondition(BBI.BrCond)) { 0
622 TII->removeBranch(*BBI.BB); 0
623 TII->insertBranch(*BBI.BB, BBI.FalseBB, BBI.TrueBB, BBI.BrCond, dl); 0
624 std::swap(BBI.TrueBB, BBI.FalseBB); 0
625 return true; 0
626 } ----
627 return false; 0
628 } 0

630 /// Returns the next block in the function blocks ordering. If it is the end, ----
631 /// returns NULL. ----
632 static inline MachineBasicBlock *getNextBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
633 MachineFunction::iterator I = MBB.getIterator(); 0
634 MachineFunction::iterator E = MBB.getParent()->end(); 0
635 if (++I == E) 0
636 return nullptr; 0
637 return &*I; 0
638 } ----

640 /// Returns true if the 'true' block (along with its predecessor) forms a valid ----
641 /// simple shape for ifcvt. It also returns the number of instructions that the ----
642 /// ifcvt would need to duplicate if performed in Dups. ----
643 bool IfConverter::ValidSimple(BBInfo &TrueBBI, unsigned &Dups, 0
644 BranchProbability Prediction) const { ----
645 Dups = 0; 0
646 if (TrueBBI.IsBeingAnalyzed || TrueBBI.IsDone) 0
647 return false; 0
648 ----
649 if (TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable) 0
650 return false; 0
651 ----
652 if (TrueBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1) { 0
653 if (TrueBBI.CannotBeCopied || 0
654 !TII->isProfitableToDupForIfCvt(*TrueBBI.BB, TrueBBI.NonPredSize, 0
655 Prediction)) ----
656 return false; 0
657 Dups = TrueBBI.NonPredSize; 0
658 } ----
659 ----
660 return true; 0
661 } ----
662 ----
663 /// Returns true if the 'true' and 'false' blocks (along with their common ----
664 /// predecessor) forms a valid triangle shape for ifcvt. If 'FalseBranch' is ----
665 /// true, it checks if 'true' block's false branch branches to the 'false' block ----
666 /// rather than the other way around. It also returns the number of instructions ----
667 /// that the ifcvt would need to duplicate if performed in 'Dups'. ----
668 bool IfConverter::ValidTriangle(BBInfo &TrueBBI, BBInfo &FalseBBI, 0
669 bool FalseBranch, unsigned &Dups, ----
670 BranchProbability Prediction) const { ----
671 Dups = 0; 0
672 if (TrueBBI.BB == FalseBBI.BB) 0
673 return false; 0
674 ----
675 if (TrueBBI.IsBeingAnalyzed || TrueBBI.IsDone) 0
676 return false; 0
677 ----
678 if (TrueBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1) { 0
679 if (TrueBBI.CannotBeCopied) 0
680 return false; 0
681 ----
682 unsigned Size = TrueBBI.NonPredSize; 0
683 if (TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable) { 0
684 if (TrueBBI.TrueBB && TrueBBI.BrCond.empty()) 0
685 // Ends with an unconditional branch. It will be removed. ----
686 --Size; 0
687 else { ----
688 MachineBasicBlock *FExit = FalseBranch 0
689 ? TrueBBI.TrueBB : TrueBBI.FalseBB; 0
690 if (FExit) 0
691 // Require a conditional branch ----
692 ++Size; 0
693 } ----
694 } ----
695 if (!TII->isProfitableToDupForIfCvt(*TrueBBI.BB, Size, Prediction)) 0
696 return false; 0
697 Dups = Size; 0
698 } ----
699 ----
700 MachineBasicBlock *TExit = FalseBranch ? TrueBBI.FalseBB : TrueBBI.TrueBB; 0
701 if (!TExit && blockAlwaysFallThrough(TrueBBI)) { 0
702 MachineFunction::iterator I = TrueBBI.BB->getIterator(); 0
703 if (++I == TrueBBI.BB->getParent()->end()) 0
704 return false; 0
705 TExit = &*I; 0
706 } ----
707 return TExit && TExit == FalseBBI.BB; 0
708 } ----
709 ----
710 /// Count duplicated instructions and move the iterators to show where they ----
711 /// are. ----
712 /// @param TIB True Iterator Begin ----
713 /// @param FIB False Iterator Begin ----
714 /// These two iterators initially point to the first instruction of the two ----
715 /// blocks, and finally point to the first non-shared instruction. ----
716 /// @param TIE True Iterator End ----
717 /// @param FIE False Iterator End ----
718 /// These two iterators initially point to End() for the two blocks() and ----
719 /// finally point to the first shared instruction in the tail. ----
720 /// Upon return [TIB, TIE), and [FIB, FIE) mark the un-duplicated portions of ----
721 /// two blocks. ----
722 /// @param Dups1 count of duplicated instructions at the beginning of the 2 ----
723 /// blocks. ----
724 /// @param Dups2 count of duplicated instructions at the end of the 2 blocks. ----
725 /// @param SkipUnconditionalBranches if true, Don't make sure that ----
726 /// unconditional branches at the end of the blocks are the same. True is ----
727 /// passed when the blocks are analyzable to allow for fallthrough to be ----
728 /// handled. ----
729 /// @return false if the shared portion prevents if conversion. ----
730 bool IfConverter::CountDuplicatedInstructions( 0
731 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &TIB, ----
732 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &FIB, ----
733 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &TIE, ----
734 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &FIE, ----
735 unsigned &Dups1, unsigned &Dups2, ----
736 MachineBasicBlock &TBB, MachineBasicBlock &FBB, ----
737 bool SkipUnconditionalBranches) const { ----
738 while (TIB != TIE && FIB != FIE) { 0
739 // Skip dbg_value instructions. These do not count. ----
740 TIB = skipDebugInstructionsForward(TIB, TIE, false); 0
741 FIB = skipDebugInstructionsForward(FIB, FIE, false); 0
742 if (TIB == TIE || FIB == FIE) 0
743 break; 0
744 if (!TIB->isIdenticalTo(*FIB)) 0
745 break; 0
746 // A pred-clobbering instruction in the shared portion prevents ----
747 // if-conversion. ----
748 std::vector PredDefs; 0
749 if (TII->ClobbersPredicate(*TIB, PredDefs, false)) 0
750 return false; 0
751 // If we get all the way to the branch instructions, don't count them. ----
752 if (!TIB->isBranch()) 0
753 ++Dups1; 0
754 ++TIB; 0
755 ++FIB; 0
756 } 0
757 ----
758 // Check for already containing all of the block. ----
759 if (TIB == TIE || FIB == FIE) 0
760 return true; 0
761 // Now, in preparation for counting duplicate instructions at the ends of the ----
762 // blocks, switch to reverse_iterators. Note that getReverse() returns an ----
763 // iterator that points to the same instruction, unlike std::reverse_iterator. ----
764 // We have to do our own shifting so that we get the same range. ----
765 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator RTIE = std::next(TIE.getReverse()); 0
766 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator RFIE = std::next(FIE.getReverse()); 0
767 const MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator RTIB = std::next(TIB.getReverse()); 0
768 const MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator RFIB = std::next(FIB.getReverse()); 0
769 ----
770 if (!TBB.succ_empty() || !FBB.succ_empty()) { 0
771 if (SkipUnconditionalBranches) { 0
772 while (RTIE != RTIB && RTIE->isUnconditionalBranch()) 0
773 ++RTIE; 0
774 while (RFIE != RFIB && RFIE->isUnconditionalBranch()) 0
775 ++RFIE; 0
776 } ----
777 } ----
778 ----
779 // Count duplicate instructions at the ends of the blocks. ----
780 while (RTIE != RTIB && RFIE != RFIB) { 0
781 // Skip dbg_value instructions. These do not count. ----
782 // Note that these are reverse iterators going forward. ----
783 RTIE = skipDebugInstructionsForward(RTIE, RTIB, false); 0
784 RFIE = skipDebugInstructionsForward(RFIE, RFIB, false); 0
785 if (RTIE == RTIB || RFIE == RFIB) 0
786 break; 0
787 if (!RTIE->isIdenticalTo(*RFIE)) 0
788 break; 0
789 // We have to verify that any branch instructions are the same, and then we ----
790 // don't count them toward the # of duplicate instructions. ----
791 if (!RTIE->isBranch()) 0
792 ++Dups2; 0
793 ++RTIE; 0
794 ++RFIE; 0
795 } ----
796 TIE = std::next(RTIE.getReverse()); 0
797 FIE = std::next(RFIE.getReverse()); 0
798 return true; 0
799 } ----
800 ----
801 /// RescanInstructions - Run ScanInstructions on a pair of blocks. ----
802 /// @param TIB - True Iterator Begin, points to first non-shared instruction ----
803 /// @param FIB - False Iterator Begin, points to first non-shared instruction ----
804 /// @param TIE - True Iterator End, points past last non-shared instruction ----
805 /// @param FIE - False Iterator End, points past last non-shared instruction ----
806 /// @param TrueBBI - BBInfo to update for the true block. ----
807 /// @param FalseBBI - BBInfo to update for the false block. ----
808 /// @returns - false if either block cannot be predicated or if both blocks end ----
809 /// with a predicate-clobbering instruction. ----
810 bool IfConverter::RescanInstructions( 0
811 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &TIB, MachineBasicBlock::iterator &FIB, ----
812 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &TIE, MachineBasicBlock::iterator &FIE, ----
813 BBInfo &TrueBBI, BBInfo &FalseBBI) const { ----
814 bool BranchUnpredicable = true; 0
815 TrueBBI.IsUnpredicable = FalseBBI.IsUnpredicable = false; 0
816 ScanInstructions(TrueBBI, TIB, TIE, BranchUnpredicable); 0
817 if (TrueBBI.IsUnpredicable) 0
818 return false; 0
819 ScanInstructions(FalseBBI, FIB, FIE, BranchUnpredicable); 0
820 if (FalseBBI.IsUnpredicable) 0
821 return false; 0
822 if (TrueBBI.ClobbersPred && FalseBBI.ClobbersPred) 0
823 return false; 0
824 return true; 0
825 } ----

827 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
828 static void verifySameBranchInstructions( 0
829 MachineBasicBlock *MBB1, ----
830 MachineBasicBlock *MBB2) { ----
831 const MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator B1 = MBB1->rend(); 0
832 const MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator B2 = MBB2->rend(); 0
833 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator E1 = MBB1->rbegin(); 0
834 MachineBasicBlock::reverse_iterator E2 = MBB2->rbegin(); 0
835 while (E1 != B1 && E2 != B2) { 0
836 skipDebugInstructionsForward(E1, B1, false); 0
837 skipDebugInstructionsForward(E2, B2, false); 0
838 if (E1 == B1 && E2 == B2) 0
839 break; 0
840 ----
841 if (E1 == B1) { 0
842 assert(!E2->isBranch() && "Branch mis-match, one block is empty."); 0
843 break; 0
844 } ----
845 if (E2 == B2) { 0
846 assert(!E1->isBranch() && "Branch mis-match, one block is empty."); 0
847 break; 0
848 } ----
849 ----
850 if (E1->isBranch() || E2->isBranch()) 0
851 assert(E1->isIdenticalTo(*E2) && 0
852 "Branch mis-match, branch instructions don't match."); ----
853 else ----
854 break; 0
855 ++E1; 0
856 ++E2; 0
857 } ----
858 } 0
859 #endif ----
