861 /// ValidForkedDiamond - Returns true if the 'true' and 'false' blocks (along ----
862 /// with their common predecessor) form a diamond if a common tail block is ----
863 /// extracted. ----
864 /// While not strictly a diamond, this pattern would form a diamond if ----
865 /// tail-merging had merged the shared tails. ----
866 /// EBB ----
867 /// _/ \_ ----
868 /// | | ----
869 /// TBB FBB ----
870 /// / \ / \ ----
871 /// FalseBB TrueBB FalseBB ----
872 /// Currently only handles analyzable branches. ----
873 /// Specifically excludes actual diamonds to avoid overlap. ----
874 bool IfConverter::ValidForkedDiamond( 0
875 BBInfo &TrueBBI, BBInfo &FalseBBI, ----
876 unsigned &Dups1, unsigned &Dups2, ----
877 BBInfo &TrueBBICalc, BBInfo &FalseBBICalc) const { ----
878 Dups1 = Dups2 = 0; 0
879 if (TrueBBI.IsBeingAnalyzed || TrueBBI.IsDone || 0
880 FalseBBI.IsBeingAnalyzed || FalseBBI.IsDone) 0
881 return false; 0
882 ----
883 if (!TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable || !FalseBBI.IsBrAnalyzable) 0
884 return false; 0
885 // Don't IfConvert blocks that can't be folded into their predecessor. ----
886 if (TrueBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1 || FalseBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1) 0
887 return false; 0
888 ----
889 // This function is specifically looking for conditional tails, as ----
890 // unconditional tails are already handled by the standard diamond case. ----
891 if (TrueBBI.BrCond.size() == 0 || 0
892 FalseBBI.BrCond.size() == 0) 0
893 return false; 0
894 ----
895 MachineBasicBlock *TT = TrueBBI.TrueBB; 0
896 MachineBasicBlock *TF = TrueBBI.FalseBB; 0
897 MachineBasicBlock *FT = FalseBBI.TrueBB; 0
898 MachineBasicBlock *FF = FalseBBI.FalseBB; 0
899 ----
900 if (!TT) 0
901 TT = getNextBlock(*TrueBBI.BB); 0
902 if (!TF) 0
903 TF = getNextBlock(*TrueBBI.BB); 0
904 if (!FT) 0
905 FT = getNextBlock(*FalseBBI.BB); 0
906 if (!FF) 0
907 FF = getNextBlock(*FalseBBI.BB); 0
908 ----
909 if (!TT || !TF) 0
910 return false; 0
911 ----
912 // Check successors. If they don't match, bail. ----
913 if (!((TT == FT && TF == FF) || (TF == FT && TT == FF))) 0
914 return false; 0
915 ----
916 bool FalseReversed = false; 0
917 if (TF == FT && TT == FF) { 0
918 // If the branches are opposing, but we can't reverse, don't do it. ----
919 if (!FalseBBI.IsBrReversible) 0
920 return false; 0
921 FalseReversed = true; 0
922 reverseBranchCondition(FalseBBI); 0
923 } ----
924 auto UnReverseOnExit = make_scope_exit([&]() { 0
925 if (FalseReversed) 0
926 reverseBranchCondition(FalseBBI); 0
927 }); 0
928 ----
929 // Count duplicate instructions at the beginning of the true and false blocks. ----
930 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIB = TrueBBI.BB->begin(); 0
931 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIB = FalseBBI.BB->begin(); 0
932 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIE = TrueBBI.BB->end(); 0
933 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIE = FalseBBI.BB->end(); 0
934 if(!CountDuplicatedInstructions(TIB, FIB, TIE, FIE, Dups1, Dups2, 0
935 *TrueBBI.BB, *FalseBBI.BB, 0
936 /* SkipUnconditionalBranches */ true)) ----
937 return false; 0
938 ----
939 TrueBBICalc.BB = TrueBBI.BB; 0
940 FalseBBICalc.BB = FalseBBI.BB; 0
941 TrueBBICalc.IsBrAnalyzable = TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable; 0
942 FalseBBICalc.IsBrAnalyzable = FalseBBI.IsBrAnalyzable; 0
943 if (!RescanInstructions(TIB, FIB, TIE, FIE, TrueBBICalc, FalseBBICalc)) 0
944 return false; 0
945 ----
946 // The size is used to decide whether to if-convert, and the shared portions ----
947 // are subtracted off. Because of the subtraction, we just use the size that ----
948 // was calculated by the original ScanInstructions, as it is correct. ----
949 TrueBBICalc.NonPredSize = TrueBBI.NonPredSize; 0
950 FalseBBICalc.NonPredSize = FalseBBI.NonPredSize; 0
951 return true; 0
952 } 0
953 ----
954 /// ValidDiamond - Returns true if the 'true' and 'false' blocks (along ----
955 /// with their common predecessor) forms a valid diamond shape for ifcvt. ----
956 bool IfConverter::ValidDiamond( 0
957 BBInfo &TrueBBI, BBInfo &FalseBBI, ----
958 unsigned &Dups1, unsigned &Dups2, ----
959 BBInfo &TrueBBICalc, BBInfo &FalseBBICalc) const { ----
960 Dups1 = Dups2 = 0; 0
961 if (TrueBBI.IsBeingAnalyzed || TrueBBI.IsDone || 0
962 FalseBBI.IsBeingAnalyzed || FalseBBI.IsDone) 0
963 return false; 0
964 ----
965 // If the True and False BBs are equal we're dealing with a degenerate case ----
966 // that we don't treat as a diamond. ----
967 if (TrueBBI.BB == FalseBBI.BB) 0
968 return false; 0
969 ----
970 MachineBasicBlock *TT = TrueBBI.TrueBB; 0
971 MachineBasicBlock *FT = FalseBBI.TrueBB; 0
972 ----
973 if (!TT && blockAlwaysFallThrough(TrueBBI)) 0
974 TT = getNextBlock(*TrueBBI.BB); 0
975 if (!FT && blockAlwaysFallThrough(FalseBBI)) 0
976 FT = getNextBlock(*FalseBBI.BB); 0
977 if (TT != FT) 0
978 return false; 0
979 if (!TT && (TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable || FalseBBI.IsBrAnalyzable)) 0
980 return false; 0
981 if (TrueBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1 || FalseBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1) 0
982 return false; 0
983 ----
984 // FIXME: Allow true block to have an early exit? ----
985 if (TrueBBI.FalseBB || FalseBBI.FalseBB) 0
986 return false; 0
987 ----
988 // Count duplicate instructions at the beginning and end of the true and ----
989 // false blocks. ----
990 // Skip unconditional branches only if we are considering an analyzable ----
991 // diamond. Otherwise the branches must be the same. ----
992 bool SkipUnconditionalBranches = 0
993 TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable && FalseBBI.IsBrAnalyzable; 0
994 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIB = TrueBBI.BB->begin(); 0
995 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIB = FalseBBI.BB->begin(); 0
996 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIE = TrueBBI.BB->end(); 0
997 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FIE = FalseBBI.BB->end(); 0
998 if(!CountDuplicatedInstructions(TIB, FIB, TIE, FIE, Dups1, Dups2, 0
999 *TrueBBI.BB, *FalseBBI.BB, 0
1000 SkipUnconditionalBranches)) ----
1001 return false; 0
1002 ----
1003 TrueBBICalc.BB = TrueBBI.BB; 0
1004 FalseBBICalc.BB = FalseBBI.BB; 0
1005 TrueBBICalc.IsBrAnalyzable = TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable; 0
1006 FalseBBICalc.IsBrAnalyzable = FalseBBI.IsBrAnalyzable; 0
1007 if (!RescanInstructions(TIB, FIB, TIE, FIE, TrueBBICalc, FalseBBICalc)) 0
1008 return false; 0
1009 // The size is used to decide whether to if-convert, and the shared portions ----
1010 // are subtracted off. Because of the subtraction, we just use the size that ----
1011 // was calculated by the original ScanInstructions, as it is correct. ----
1012 TrueBBICalc.NonPredSize = TrueBBI.NonPredSize; 0
1013 FalseBBICalc.NonPredSize = FalseBBI.NonPredSize; 0
1014 return true; 0
1015 } ----
1016 ----
1017 /// AnalyzeBranches - Look at the branches at the end of a block to determine if ----
1018 /// the block is predicable. ----
1019 void IfConverter::AnalyzeBranches(BBInfo &BBI) { 0
1020 if (BBI.IsDone) 0
1021 return; 0
1022 ----
1023 BBI.TrueBB = BBI.FalseBB = nullptr; 0
1024 BBI.BrCond.clear(); 0
1025 BBI.IsBrAnalyzable = 0
1026 !TII->analyzeBranch(*BBI.BB, BBI.TrueBB, BBI.FalseBB, BBI.BrCond); 0
1027 if (!BBI.IsBrAnalyzable) { 0
1028 BBI.TrueBB = nullptr; 0
1029 BBI.FalseBB = nullptr; 0
1030 BBI.BrCond.clear(); 0
1031 } ----
1032 ----
1033 SmallVector RevCond(BBI.BrCond.begin(), BBI.BrCond.end()); 0
1034 BBI.IsBrReversible = (RevCond.size() == 0) || 0
1035 !TII->reverseBranchCondition(RevCond); 0
1036 BBI.HasFallThrough = BBI.IsBrAnalyzable && BBI.FalseBB == nullptr; 0
1037 ----
1038 if (BBI.BrCond.size()) { 0
1039 // No false branch. This BB must end with a conditional branch and a ----
1040 // fallthrough. ----
1041 if (!BBI.FalseBB) 0
1042 BBI.FalseBB = findFalseBlock(BBI.BB, BBI.TrueBB); 0
1043 if (!BBI.FalseBB) { 0
1044 // Malformed bcc? True and false blocks are the same? ----
1045 BBI.IsUnpredicable = true; 0
1046 } ----
1047 } ----
1048 } 0
1049 ----
1050 /// ScanInstructions - Scan all the instructions in the block to determine if ----
1051 /// the block is predicable. In most cases, that means all the instructions ----
1052 /// in the block are isPredicable(). Also checks if the block contains any ----
1053 /// instruction which can clobber a predicate (e.g. condition code register). ----
1054 /// If so, the block is not predicable unless it's the last instruction. ----
1055 void IfConverter::ScanInstructions(BBInfo &BBI, 0
1056 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &Begin, ----
1057 MachineBasicBlock::iterator &End, ----
1058 bool BranchUnpredicable) const { ----
1059 if (BBI.IsDone || BBI.IsUnpredicable) 0
1060 return; 0
1061 ----
1062 bool AlreadyPredicated = !BBI.Predicate.empty(); 0
1063 ----
1064 BBI.NonPredSize = 0; 0
1065 BBI.ExtraCost = 0; 0
1066 BBI.ExtraCost2 = 0; 0
1067 BBI.ClobbersPred = false; 0
1068 for (MachineInstr &MI : make_range(Begin, End)) { 0
1069 if (MI.isDebugInstr()) 0
1070 continue; 0
1071 ----
1072 // It's unsafe to duplicate convergent instructions in this context, so set ----
1073 // BBI.CannotBeCopied to true if MI is convergent. To see why, consider the ----
1074 // following CFG, which is subject to our "simple" transformation. ----
1075 // ----
1076 // BB0 // if (c1) goto BB1; else goto BB2; ----
1077 // / \ ----
1078 // BB1 | ----
1079 // | BB2 // if (c2) goto TBB; else goto FBB; ----
1080 // | / | ----
1081 // | / | ----
1082 // TBB | ----
1083 // | | ----
1084 // | FBB ----
1085 // | ----
1086 // exit ----
1087 // ----
1088 // Suppose we want to move TBB's contents up into BB1 and BB2 (in BB1 they'd ----
1089 // be unconditional, and in BB2, they'd be predicated upon c2), and suppose ----
1090 // TBB contains a convergent instruction. This is safe iff doing so does ----
1091 // not add a control-flow dependency to the convergent instruction -- i.e., ----
1092 // it's safe iff the set of control flows that leads us to the convergent ----
1093 // instruction does not get smaller after the transformation. ----
1094 // ----
1095 // Originally we executed TBB if c1 || c2. After the transformation, there ----
1096 // are two copies of TBB's instructions. We get to the first if c1, and we ----
1097 // get to the second if !c1 && c2. ----
1098 // ----
1099 // There are clearly fewer ways to satisfy the condition "c1" than ----
1100 // "c1 || c2". Since we've shrunk the set of control flows which lead to ----
1101 // our convergent instruction, the transformation is unsafe. ----
1102 if (MI.isNotDuplicable() || MI.isConvergent()) 0
1103 BBI.CannotBeCopied = true; 0
1104 ----
1105 bool isPredicated = TII->isPredicated(MI); 0
1106 bool isCondBr = BBI.IsBrAnalyzable && MI.isConditionalBranch(); 0
1107 ----
1108 if (BranchUnpredicable && MI.isBranch()) { 0
1109 BBI.IsUnpredicable = true; 0
1110 return; 0
1111 } ----
1112 ----
1113 // A conditional branch is not predicable, but it may be eliminated. ----
1114 if (isCondBr) 0
1115 continue; 0
1116 ----
1117 if (!isPredicated) { 0
1118 BBI.NonPredSize++; 0
1119 unsigned ExtraPredCost = TII->getPredicationCost(MI); 0
1120 unsigned NumCycles = SchedModel.computeInstrLatency(&MI, false); 0
1121 if (NumCycles > 1) 0
1122 BBI.ExtraCost += NumCycles-1; 0
1123 BBI.ExtraCost2 += ExtraPredCost; 0
1124 } else if (!AlreadyPredicated) { 0
1125 // FIXME: This instruction is already predicated before the ----
1126 // if-conversion pass. It's probably something like a conditional move. ----
1127 // Mark this block unpredicable for now. ----
1128 BBI.IsUnpredicable = true; 0
1129 return; 0
1130 } ----
1131 ----
1132 if (BBI.ClobbersPred && !isPredicated) { 0
1133 // Predicate modification instruction should end the block (except for ----
1134 // already predicated instructions and end of block branches). ----
1135 // Predicate may have been modified, the subsequent (currently) ----
1136 // unpredicated instructions cannot be correctly predicated. ----
1137 BBI.IsUnpredicable = true; 0
1138 return; 0
1139 } ----
1140 ----
1141 // FIXME: Make use of PredDefs? e.g. ADDC, SUBC sets predicates but are ----
1142 // still potentially predicable. ----
1143 std::vector PredDefs; 0
1144 if (TII->ClobbersPredicate(MI, PredDefs, true)) 0
1145 BBI.ClobbersPred = true; 0
1146 ----
1147 if (!TII->isPredicable(MI)) { 0
1148 BBI.IsUnpredicable = true; 0
1149 return; 0
1150 } ----
1151 } 0
1152 } ----
1153 ----
1154 /// Determine if the block is a suitable candidate to be predicated by the ----
1155 /// specified predicate. ----
1156 /// @param BBI BBInfo for the block to check ----
1157 /// @param Pred Predicate array for the branch that leads to BBI ----
1158 /// @param isTriangle true if the Analysis is for a triangle ----
1159 /// @param RevBranch true if Reverse(Pred) leads to BBI (e.g. BBI is the false ----
1160 /// case ----
1161 /// @param hasCommonTail true if BBI shares a tail with a sibling block that ----
1162 /// contains any instruction that would make the block unpredicable. ----
1163 bool IfConverter::FeasibilityAnalysis(BBInfo &BBI, 0
1164 SmallVectorImpl &Pred, ----
1165 bool isTriangle, bool RevBranch, ----
1166 bool hasCommonTail) { ----
1167 // If the block is dead or unpredicable, then it cannot be predicated. ----
1168 // Two blocks may share a common unpredicable tail, but this doesn't prevent ----
1169 // them from being if-converted. The non-shared portion is assumed to have ----
1170 // been checked ----
1171 if (BBI.IsDone || (BBI.IsUnpredicable && !hasCommonTail)) 0
1172 return false; 0
1173 ----
1174 // If it is already predicated but we couldn't analyze its terminator, the ----
1175 // latter might fallthrough, but we can't determine where to. ----
1176 // Conservatively avoid if-converting again. ----
1177 if (BBI.Predicate.size() && !BBI.IsBrAnalyzable) 0
1178 return false; 0
1179 ----
1180 // If it is already predicated, check if the new predicate subsumes ----
1181 // its predicate. ----
1182 if (BBI.Predicate.size() && !TII->SubsumesPredicate(Pred, BBI.Predicate)) 0
1183 return false; 0
1184 ----
1185 if (!hasCommonTail && BBI.BrCond.size()) { 0
1186 if (!isTriangle) 0
1187 return false; 0
1188 ----
1189 // Test predicate subsumption. ----
1190 SmallVector RevPred(Pred.begin(), Pred.end()); 0
1191 SmallVector Cond(BBI.BrCond.begin(), BBI.BrCond.end()); 0
1192 if (RevBranch) { 0
1193 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(Cond)) 0
1194 return false; 0
1195 } ----
1196 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(RevPred) || 0
1197 !TII->SubsumesPredicate(Cond, RevPred)) 0
1198 return false; 0
1199 } 0
1200 ----
1201 return true; 0
1202 } ----
1203 ----
1204 /// Analyze the structure of the sub-CFG starting from the specified block. ----
1205 /// Record its successors and whether it looks like an if-conversion candidate. ----
1206 void IfConverter::AnalyzeBlock( 0
1207 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, std::vector> &Tokens) { ----
1208 struct BBState { ----
1209 BBState(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) : MBB(&MBB) {} 0
1210 MachineBasicBlock *MBB; ----
1211 ----
1212 /// This flag is true if MBB's successors have been analyzed. ----
1213 bool SuccsAnalyzed = false; ----
1214 }; ----
1215 ----
1216 // Push MBB to the stack. ----
1217 SmallVector BBStack(1, MBB); 0
1218 ----
1219 while (!BBStack.empty()) { 0
1220 BBState &State = BBStack.back(); 0
1221 MachineBasicBlock *BB = State.MBB; 0
1222 BBInfo &BBI = BBAnalysis[BB->getNumber()]; 0
1223 ----
1224 if (!State.SuccsAnalyzed) { 0
1225 if (BBI.IsAnalyzed || BBI.IsBeingAnalyzed) { 0
1226 BBStack.pop_back(); 0
1227 continue; 0
1228 } ----
1229 ----
1230 BBI.BB = BB; 0
1231 BBI.IsBeingAnalyzed = true; 0
1232 ----
1233 AnalyzeBranches(BBI); 0
1234 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Begin = BBI.BB->begin(); 0
1235 MachineBasicBlock::iterator End = BBI.BB->end(); 0
1236 ScanInstructions(BBI, Begin, End); 0
1237 ----
1238 // Unanalyzable or ends with fallthrough or unconditional branch, or if is ----
1239 // not considered for ifcvt anymore. ----
1240 if (!BBI.IsBrAnalyzable || BBI.BrCond.empty() || BBI.IsDone) { 0
1241 BBI.IsBeingAnalyzed = false; 0
1242 BBI.IsAnalyzed = true; 0
1243 BBStack.pop_back(); 0
1244 continue; 0
1245 } ----
1246 ----
1247 // Do not ifcvt if either path is a back edge to the entry block. ----
1248 if (BBI.TrueBB == BB || BBI.FalseBB == BB) { 0
1249 BBI.IsBeingAnalyzed = false; 0
1250 BBI.IsAnalyzed = true; 0
1251 BBStack.pop_back(); 0
1252 continue; 0
1253 } ----
1254 ----
1255 // Do not ifcvt if true and false fallthrough blocks are the same. ----
1256 if (!BBI.FalseBB) { 0
1257 BBI.IsBeingAnalyzed = false; 0
1258 BBI.IsAnalyzed = true; 0
1259 BBStack.pop_back(); 0
1260 continue; 0
1261 } ----
1262 ----
1263 // Push the False and True blocks to the stack. ----
1264 State.SuccsAnalyzed = true; 0
1265 BBStack.push_back(*BBI.FalseBB); 0
1266 BBStack.push_back(*BBI.TrueBB); 0
1267 continue; 0
1268 } 0
1269 ----
1270 BBInfo &TrueBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.TrueBB->getNumber()]; 0
1271 BBInfo &FalseBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.FalseBB->getNumber()]; 0
1272 ----
1273 if (TrueBBI.IsDone && FalseBBI.IsDone) { 0
1274 BBI.IsBeingAnalyzed = false; 0
1275 BBI.IsAnalyzed = true; 0
1276 BBStack.pop_back(); 0
1277 continue; 0
1278 } ----
1279 ----
1280 SmallVector ----
1281 RevCond(BBI.BrCond.begin(), BBI.BrCond.end()); 0
1282 bool CanRevCond = !TII->reverseBranchCondition(RevCond); 0
1283 ----
1284 unsigned Dups = 0; 0
1285 unsigned Dups2 = 0; 0
1286 bool TNeedSub = !TrueBBI.Predicate.empty(); 0
1287 bool FNeedSub = !FalseBBI.Predicate.empty(); 0
1288 bool Enqueued = false; 0
1289 ----
1290 BranchProbability Prediction = MBPI->getEdgeProbability(BB, TrueBBI.BB); 0
1291 ----
1292 if (CanRevCond) { 0
1293 BBInfo TrueBBICalc, FalseBBICalc; 0
1294 auto feasibleDiamond = [&](bool Forked) { 0
1295 bool MeetsSize = MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(TrueBBICalc, FalseBBICalc, *BB, 0
1296 Dups + Dups2, Prediction, Forked); 0
1297 bool TrueFeasible = FeasibilityAnalysis(TrueBBI, BBI.BrCond, 0
1298 /* IsTriangle */ false, /* RevCond */ false, ----
1299 /* hasCommonTail */ true); ----
1300 bool FalseFeasible = FeasibilityAnalysis(FalseBBI, RevCond, 0
1301 /* IsTriangle */ false, /* RevCond */ false, ----
1302 /* hasCommonTail */ true); ----
1303 return MeetsSize && TrueFeasible && FalseFeasible; 0
1304 }; 0
1305 ----
1306 if (ValidDiamond(TrueBBI, FalseBBI, Dups, Dups2, 0
1307 TrueBBICalc, FalseBBICalc)) { ----
1308 if (feasibleDiamond(false)) { 0
1309 // Diamond: ----
1310 // EBB ----
1311 // / \_ ----
1312 // | | ----
1313 // TBB FBB ----
1314 // \ / ----
1315 // TailBB ----
1316 // Note TailBB can be empty. ----
1317 Tokens.push_back(std::make_unique( 0
1318 BBI, ICDiamond, TNeedSub | FNeedSub, Dups, Dups2, 0
1319 (bool) TrueBBICalc.ClobbersPred, (bool) FalseBBICalc.ClobbersPred)); 0
1320 Enqueued = true; 0
1321 } ----
1322 } else if (ValidForkedDiamond(TrueBBI, FalseBBI, Dups, Dups2, 0
1323 TrueBBICalc, FalseBBICalc)) { ----
1324 if (feasibleDiamond(true)) { 0
1325 // ForkedDiamond: ----
1326 // if TBB and FBB have a common tail that includes their conditional ----
1327 // branch instructions, then we can If Convert this pattern. ----
1328 // EBB ----
1329 // _/ \_ ----
1330 // | | ----
1331 // TBB FBB ----
1332 // / \ / \ ----
1333 // FalseBB TrueBB FalseBB ----
1334 // ----
1335 Tokens.push_back(std::make_unique( 0
1336 BBI, ICForkedDiamond, TNeedSub | FNeedSub, Dups, Dups2, 0
1337 (bool) TrueBBICalc.ClobbersPred, (bool) FalseBBICalc.ClobbersPred)); 0
1338 Enqueued = true; 0
1339 } ----
1340 } ----
1341 } 0
1342 ----
1343 if (ValidTriangle(TrueBBI, FalseBBI, false, Dups, Prediction) && 0
1344 MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(*TrueBBI.BB, TrueBBI.NonPredSize + TrueBBI.ExtraCost, 0
1345 TrueBBI.ExtraCost2, Prediction) && 0
1346 FeasibilityAnalysis(TrueBBI, BBI.BrCond, true)) { 0
1347 // Triangle: ----
1348 // EBB ----
1349 // | \_ ----
1350 // | | ----
1351 // | TBB ----
1352 // | / ----
1353 // FBB ----
1354 Tokens.push_back( 0
1355 std::make_unique(BBI, ICTriangle, TNeedSub, Dups)); 0
1356 Enqueued = true; 0
1357 } ----
1358 ----
1359 if (ValidTriangle(TrueBBI, FalseBBI, true, Dups, Prediction) && 0
1360 MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(*TrueBBI.BB, TrueBBI.NonPredSize + TrueBBI.ExtraCost, 0
1361 TrueBBI.ExtraCost2, Prediction) && 0
1362 FeasibilityAnalysis(TrueBBI, BBI.BrCond, true, true)) { 0
1363 Tokens.push_back( 0
1364 std::make_unique(BBI, ICTriangleRev, TNeedSub, Dups)); 0
1365 Enqueued = true; 0
1366 } ----
1367 ----
1368 if (ValidSimple(TrueBBI, Dups, Prediction) && 0
1369 MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(*TrueBBI.BB, TrueBBI.NonPredSize + TrueBBI.ExtraCost, 0
1370 TrueBBI.ExtraCost2, Prediction) && 0
1371 FeasibilityAnalysis(TrueBBI, BBI.BrCond)) { 0
1372 // Simple (split, no rejoin): ----
1373 // EBB ----
1374 // | \_ ----
1375 // | | ----
1376 // | TBB---> exit ----
1377 // | ----
1378 // FBB ----
1379 Tokens.push_back( 0
1380 std::make_unique(BBI, ICSimple, TNeedSub, Dups)); 0
1381 Enqueued = true; 0
1382 } ----
1383 ----
1384 if (CanRevCond) { 0
1385 // Try the other path... ----
1386 if (ValidTriangle(FalseBBI, TrueBBI, false, Dups, 0
1387 Prediction.getCompl()) && 0
1388 MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(*FalseBBI.BB, 0
1389 FalseBBI.NonPredSize + FalseBBI.ExtraCost, 0
1390 FalseBBI.ExtraCost2, Prediction.getCompl()) && 0
1391 FeasibilityAnalysis(FalseBBI, RevCond, true)) { 0
1392 Tokens.push_back(std::make_unique(BBI, ICTriangleFalse, 0
1393 FNeedSub, Dups)); ----
1394 Enqueued = true; 0
1395 } ----
1396 ----
1397 if (ValidTriangle(FalseBBI, TrueBBI, true, Dups, 0
1398 Prediction.getCompl()) && 0
1399 MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(*FalseBBI.BB, 0
1400 FalseBBI.NonPredSize + FalseBBI.ExtraCost, 0
1401 FalseBBI.ExtraCost2, Prediction.getCompl()) && 0
1402 FeasibilityAnalysis(FalseBBI, RevCond, true, true)) { 0
1403 Tokens.push_back( 0
1404 std::make_unique(BBI, ICTriangleFRev, FNeedSub, Dups)); 0
1405 Enqueued = true; 0
1406 } ----
1407 ----
1408 if (ValidSimple(FalseBBI, Dups, Prediction.getCompl()) && 0
1409 MeetIfcvtSizeLimit(*FalseBBI.BB, 0
1410 FalseBBI.NonPredSize + FalseBBI.ExtraCost, 0
1411 FalseBBI.ExtraCost2, Prediction.getCompl()) && 0
1412 FeasibilityAnalysis(FalseBBI, RevCond)) { 0
1413 Tokens.push_back( 0
1414 std::make_unique(BBI, ICSimpleFalse, FNeedSub, Dups)); 0
1415 Enqueued = true; 0
1416 } ----
1417 } ----
1418 ----
1419 BBI.IsEnqueued = Enqueued; 0
1420 BBI.IsBeingAnalyzed = false; 0
1421 BBI.IsAnalyzed = true; 0
1422 BBStack.pop_back(); 0
1423 } 0
1424 } 0
1425 ----
1426 /// Analyze all blocks and find entries for all if-conversion candidates. ----
1427 void IfConverter::AnalyzeBlocks( 0
1428 MachineFunction &MF, std::vector> &Tokens) { ----
1429 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) 0
1430 AnalyzeBlock(MBB, Tokens); 0
1431 ----
1432 // Sort to favor more complex ifcvt scheme. ----
1433 llvm::stable_sort(Tokens, IfcvtTokenCmp); 0
1434 } 0
1435 ----
1436 /// Returns true either if ToMBB is the next block after MBB or that all the ----
1437 /// intervening blocks are empty (given MBB can fall through to its next block). ----
1438 static bool canFallThroughTo(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock &ToMBB) { 0
1439 MachineFunction::iterator PI = MBB.getIterator(); 0
1440 MachineFunction::iterator I = std::next(PI); 0
1441 MachineFunction::iterator TI = ToMBB.getIterator(); 0
1442 MachineFunction::iterator E = MBB.getParent()->end(); 0
1443 while (I != TI) { 0
1444 // Check isSuccessor to avoid case where the next block is empty, but ----
1445 // it's not a successor. ----
1446 if (I == E || !I->empty() || !PI->isSuccessor(&*I)) 0
1447 return false; 0
1448 PI = I++; 0
1449 } ----
1450 // Finally see if the last I is indeed a successor to PI. ----
1451 return PI->isSuccessor(&*I); 0
1452 } ----
1453 ----
1454 /// Invalidate predecessor BB info so it would be re-analyzed to determine if it ----
1455 /// can be if-converted. If predecessor is already enqueued, dequeue it! ----
1456 void IfConverter::InvalidatePreds(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1457 for (const MachineBasicBlock *Predecessor : MBB.predecessors()) { 0
1458 BBInfo &PBBI = BBAnalysis[Predecessor->getNumber()]; 0
1459 if (PBBI.IsDone || PBBI.BB == &MBB) 0
1460 continue; 0
1461 PBBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1462 PBBI.IsEnqueued = false; 0
1463 } ----
1464 } 0
1465 ----
1466 /// Inserts an unconditional branch from \p MBB to \p ToMBB. ----
1467 static void InsertUncondBranch(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, MachineBasicBlock &ToMBB, 0
1468 const TargetInstrInfo *TII) { ----
1469 DebugLoc dl; // FIXME: this is nowhere 0
1470 SmallVector NoCond; 0
1471 TII->insertBranch(MBB, &ToMBB, nullptr, NoCond, dl); 0
1472 } 0
1473 ----
1474 /// Behaves like LiveRegUnits::StepForward() but also adds implicit uses to all ----
1475 /// values defined in MI which are also live/used by MI. ----
1476 static void UpdatePredRedefs(MachineInstr &MI, LivePhysRegs &Redefs) { 0
1477 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI = MI.getMF()->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo(); 0
1478 ----
1479 // Before stepping forward past MI, remember which regs were live ----
1480 // before MI. This is needed to set the Undef flag only when reg is ----
1481 // dead. ----
1482 SparseSet> LiveBeforeMI; 0
1483 LiveBeforeMI.setUniverse(TRI->getNumRegs()); 0
1484 for (unsigned Reg : Redefs) 0
1485 LiveBeforeMI.insert(Reg); 0
1486 ----
1487 SmallVector, 4> Clobbers; 0
1488 Redefs.stepForward(MI, Clobbers); 0
1489 ----
1490 // Now add the implicit uses for each of the clobbered values. ----
1491 for (auto Clobber : Clobbers) { 0
1492 // FIXME: Const cast here is nasty, but better than making StepForward ----
1493 // take a mutable instruction instead of const. ----
1494 unsigned Reg = Clobber.first; 0
1495 MachineOperand &Op = const_cast(*Clobber.second); 0
1496 MachineInstr *OpMI = Op.getParent(); 0
1497 MachineInstrBuilder MIB(*OpMI->getMF(), OpMI); 0
1498 if (Op.isRegMask()) { 0
1499 // First handle regmasks. They clobber any entries in the mask which ----
1500 // means that we need a def for those registers. ----
1501 if (LiveBeforeMI.count(Reg)) 0
1502 MIB.addReg(Reg, RegState::Implicit); 0
1503 ----
1504 // We also need to add an implicit def of this register for the later ----
1505 // use to read from. ----
1506 // For the register allocator to have allocated a register clobbered ----
1507 // by the call which is used later, it must be the case that ----
1508 // the call doesn't return. ----
1509 MIB.addReg(Reg, RegState::Implicit | RegState::Define); 0
1510 continue; 0
1511 } ----
1512 if (any_of(TRI->subregs_inclusive(Reg), 0
1513 [&](MCPhysReg S) { return LiveBeforeMI.count(S); })) 0
1514 MIB.addReg(Reg, RegState::Implicit); 0
1515 } ----
1516 } 0
1517 ----
1518 /// If convert a simple (split, no rejoin) sub-CFG. ----
1519 bool IfConverter::IfConvertSimple(BBInfo &BBI, IfcvtKind Kind) { 0
1520 BBInfo &TrueBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.TrueBB->getNumber()]; 0
1521 BBInfo &FalseBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.FalseBB->getNumber()]; 0
1522 BBInfo *CvtBBI = &TrueBBI; 0
1523 BBInfo *NextBBI = &FalseBBI; 0
1524 ----
1525 SmallVector Cond(BBI.BrCond.begin(), BBI.BrCond.end()); 0
1526 if (Kind == ICSimpleFalse) 0
1527 std::swap(CvtBBI, NextBBI); 0
1528 ----
1529 MachineBasicBlock &CvtMBB = *CvtBBI->BB; 0
1530 MachineBasicBlock &NextMBB = *NextBBI->BB; 0
1531 if (CvtBBI->IsDone || 0
1532 (CvtBBI->CannotBeCopied && CvtMBB.pred_size() > 1)) { 0
1533 // Something has changed. It's no longer safe to predicate this block. ----
1534 BBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1535 CvtBBI->IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1536 return false; 0
1537 } ----
1538 ----
1539 if (CvtMBB.hasAddressTaken()) 0
1540 // Conservatively abort if-conversion if BB's address is taken. ----
1541 return false; 0
1542 ----
1543 if (Kind == ICSimpleFalse) 0
1544 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(Cond)) 0
1545 llvm_unreachable("Unable to reverse branch condition!"); 0
1546 ----
1547 Redefs.init(*TRI); 0
1548 ----
1549 if (MRI->tracksLiveness()) { 0
1550 // Initialize liveins to the first BB. These are potentially redefined by ----
1551 // predicated instructions. ----
1552 Redefs.addLiveInsNoPristines(CvtMBB); 0
1553 Redefs.addLiveInsNoPristines(NextMBB); 0
1554 } ----
1555 ----
1556 // Remove the branches from the entry so we can add the contents of the true ----
1557 // block to it. ----
1558 BBI.NonPredSize -= TII->removeBranch(*BBI.BB); 0
1559 ----
1560 if (CvtMBB.pred_size() > 1) { 0
1561 // Copy instructions in the true block, predicate them, and add them to ----
1562 // the entry block. ----
1563 CopyAndPredicateBlock(BBI, *CvtBBI, Cond); 0
1564 ----
1565 // Keep the CFG updated. ----
1566 BBI.BB->removeSuccessor(&CvtMBB, true); 0
1567 } else { ----
1568 // Predicate the instructions in the true block. ----
1569 PredicateBlock(*CvtBBI, CvtMBB.end(), Cond); 0
1570 ----
1571 // Merge converted block into entry block. The BB to Cvt edge is removed ----
1572 // by MergeBlocks. ----
1573 MergeBlocks(BBI, *CvtBBI); 0
1574 } ----
1575 ----
1576 bool IterIfcvt = true; 0
1577 if (!canFallThroughTo(*BBI.BB, NextMBB)) { 0
1578 InsertUncondBranch(*BBI.BB, NextMBB, TII); 0
1579 BBI.HasFallThrough = false; 0
1580 // Now ifcvt'd block will look like this: ----
1581 // BB: ----
1582 // ... ----
1583 // t, f = cmp ----
1584 // if t op ----
1585 // b BBf ----
1586 // ----
1587 // We cannot further ifcvt this block because the unconditional branch ----
1588 // will have to be predicated on the new condition, that will not be ----
1589 // available if cmp executes. ----
1590 IterIfcvt = false; 0
1591 } ----
1592 ----
1593 // Update block info. BB can be iteratively if-converted. ----
1594 if (!IterIfcvt) 0
1595 BBI.IsDone = true; 0
1596 InvalidatePreds(*BBI.BB); 0
1597 CvtBBI->IsDone = true; 0
1598 ----
1599 // FIXME: Must maintain LiveIns. ----
1600 return true; 0
1601 } 0
1602 ----
1603 /// If convert a triangle sub-CFG. ----
1604 bool IfConverter::IfConvertTriangle(BBInfo &BBI, IfcvtKind Kind) { 0
1605 BBInfo &TrueBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.TrueBB->getNumber()]; 0
1606 BBInfo &FalseBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.FalseBB->getNumber()]; 0
1607 BBInfo *CvtBBI = &TrueBBI; 0
1608 BBInfo *NextBBI = &FalseBBI; 0
1609 DebugLoc dl; // FIXME: this is nowhere 0
1610 ----
1611 SmallVector Cond(BBI.BrCond.begin(), BBI.BrCond.end()); 0
1612 if (Kind == ICTriangleFalse || Kind == ICTriangleFRev) 0
1613 std::swap(CvtBBI, NextBBI); 0
1614 ----
1615 MachineBasicBlock &CvtMBB = *CvtBBI->BB; 0
1616 MachineBasicBlock &NextMBB = *NextBBI->BB; 0
1617 if (CvtBBI->IsDone || 0
1618 (CvtBBI->CannotBeCopied && CvtMBB.pred_size() > 1)) { 0
1619 // Something has changed. It's no longer safe to predicate this block. ----
1620 BBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1621 CvtBBI->IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1622 return false; 0
1623 } ----
1624 ----
1625 if (CvtMBB.hasAddressTaken()) 0
1626 // Conservatively abort if-conversion if BB's address is taken. ----
1627 return false; 0
1628 ----
1629 if (Kind == ICTriangleFalse || Kind == ICTriangleFRev) 0
1630 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(Cond)) 0
1631 llvm_unreachable("Unable to reverse branch condition!"); 0
1632 ----
1633 if (Kind == ICTriangleRev || Kind == ICTriangleFRev) { 0
1634 if (reverseBranchCondition(*CvtBBI)) { 0
1635 // BB has been changed, modify its predecessors (except for this ----
1636 // one) so they don't get ifcvt'ed based on bad intel. ----
1637 for (MachineBasicBlock *PBB : CvtMBB.predecessors()) { 0
1638 if (PBB == BBI.BB) 0
1639 continue; 0
1640 BBInfo &PBBI = BBAnalysis[PBB->getNumber()]; 0
1641 if (PBBI.IsEnqueued) { 0
1642 PBBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1643 PBBI.IsEnqueued = false; 0
1644 } ----
1645 } ----
1646 } ----
1647 } ----
1648 ----
1649 // Initialize liveins to the first BB. These are potentially redefined by ----
1650 // predicated instructions. ----
1651 Redefs.init(*TRI); 0
1652 if (MRI->tracksLiveness()) { 0
1653 Redefs.addLiveInsNoPristines(CvtMBB); 0
1654 Redefs.addLiveInsNoPristines(NextMBB); 0
1655 } ----
1656 ----
1657 bool HasEarlyExit = CvtBBI->FalseBB != nullptr; 0
1658 BranchProbability CvtNext, CvtFalse, BBNext, BBCvt; 0
1659 ----
1660 if (HasEarlyExit) { 0
1661 // Get probabilities before modifying CvtMBB and BBI.BB. ----
1662 CvtNext = MBPI->getEdgeProbability(&CvtMBB, &NextMBB); 0
1663 CvtFalse = MBPI->getEdgeProbability(&CvtMBB, CvtBBI->FalseBB); 0
1664 BBNext = MBPI->getEdgeProbability(BBI.BB, &NextMBB); 0
1665 BBCvt = MBPI->getEdgeProbability(BBI.BB, &CvtMBB); 0
1666 } ----
1667 ----
1668 // Remove the branches from the entry so we can add the contents of the true ----
1669 // block to it. ----
1670 BBI.NonPredSize -= TII->removeBranch(*BBI.BB); 0
1671 ----
1672 if (CvtMBB.pred_size() > 1) { 0
1673 // Copy instructions in the true block, predicate them, and add them to ----
1674 // the entry block. ----
1675 CopyAndPredicateBlock(BBI, *CvtBBI, Cond, true); 0
1676 } else { ----
1677 // Predicate the 'true' block after removing its branch. ----
1678 CvtBBI->NonPredSize -= TII->removeBranch(CvtMBB); 0
1679 PredicateBlock(*CvtBBI, CvtMBB.end(), Cond); 0
1680 ----
1681 // Now merge the entry of the triangle with the true block. ----
1682 MergeBlocks(BBI, *CvtBBI, false); 0
1683 } ----
1684 ----
1685 // Keep the CFG updated. ----
1686 BBI.BB->removeSuccessor(&CvtMBB, true); 0
1687 ----
1688 // If 'true' block has a 'false' successor, add an exit branch to it. ----
1689 if (HasEarlyExit) { 0
1690 SmallVector RevCond(CvtBBI->BrCond.begin(), ----
1691 CvtBBI->BrCond.end()); 0
1692 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(RevCond)) 0
1693 llvm_unreachable("Unable to reverse branch condition!"); 0
1694 ----
1695 // Update the edge probability for both CvtBBI->FalseBB and NextBBI. ----
1696 // NewNext = New_Prob(BBI.BB, NextMBB) = ----
1697 // Prob(BBI.BB, NextMBB) + ----
1698 // Prob(BBI.BB, CvtMBB) * Prob(CvtMBB, NextMBB) ----
1699 // NewFalse = New_Prob(BBI.BB, CvtBBI->FalseBB) = ----
1700 // Prob(BBI.BB, CvtMBB) * Prob(CvtMBB, CvtBBI->FalseBB) ----
1701 auto NewTrueBB = getNextBlock(*BBI.BB); 0
1702 auto NewNext = BBNext + BBCvt * CvtNext; 0
1703 auto NewTrueBBIter = find(BBI.BB->successors(), NewTrueBB); 0
1704 if (NewTrueBBIter != BBI.BB->succ_end()) 0
1705 BBI.BB->setSuccProbability(NewTrueBBIter, NewNext); 0
1706 ----
1707 auto NewFalse = BBCvt * CvtFalse; 0
1708 TII->insertBranch(*BBI.BB, CvtBBI->FalseBB, nullptr, RevCond, dl); 0
1709 BBI.BB->addSuccessor(CvtBBI->FalseBB, NewFalse); 0
1710 } 0
1711 ----
1712 // Merge in the 'false' block if the 'false' block has no other ----
1713 // predecessors. Otherwise, add an unconditional branch to 'false'. ----
1714 bool FalseBBDead = false; 0
1715 bool IterIfcvt = true; 0
1716 bool isFallThrough = canFallThroughTo(*BBI.BB, NextMBB); 0
1717 if (!isFallThrough) { 0
1718 // Only merge them if the true block does not fallthrough to the false ----
1719 // block. By not merging them, we make it possible to iteratively ----
1720 // ifcvt the blocks. ----
1721 if (!HasEarlyExit && 0
1722 NextMBB.pred_size() == 1 && !NextBBI->HasFallThrough && 0
1723 !NextMBB.hasAddressTaken()) { 0
1724 MergeBlocks(BBI, *NextBBI); 0
1725 FalseBBDead = true; 0
1726 } else { ----
1727 InsertUncondBranch(*BBI.BB, NextMBB, TII); 0
1728 BBI.HasFallThrough = false; 0
1729 } ----
1730 // Mixed predicated and unpredicated code. This cannot be iteratively ----
1731 // predicated. ----
1732 IterIfcvt = false; 0
1733 } ----
1734 ----
1735 // Update block info. BB can be iteratively if-converted. ----
1736 if (!IterIfcvt) 0
1737 BBI.IsDone = true; 0
1738 InvalidatePreds(*BBI.BB); 0
1739 CvtBBI->IsDone = true; 0
1740 if (FalseBBDead) 0
1741 NextBBI->IsDone = true; 0
1742 ----
1743 // FIXME: Must maintain LiveIns. ----
1744 return true; 0
1745 } 0
1746 ----
1747 /// Common code shared between diamond conversions. ----
1748 /// \p BBI, \p TrueBBI, and \p FalseBBI form the diamond shape. ----
1749 /// \p NumDups1 - number of shared instructions at the beginning of \p TrueBBI ----
1750 /// and FalseBBI ----
1751 /// \p NumDups2 - number of shared instructions at the end of \p TrueBBI ----
1752 /// and \p FalseBBI ----
1753 /// \p RemoveBranch - Remove the common branch of the two blocks before ----
1754 /// predicating. Only false for unanalyzable fallthrough ----
1755 /// cases. The caller will replace the branch if necessary. ----
1756 /// \p MergeAddEdges - Add successor edges when merging blocks. Only false for ----
1757 /// unanalyzable fallthrough ----
1758 bool IfConverter::IfConvertDiamondCommon( 0
1759 BBInfo &BBI, BBInfo &TrueBBI, BBInfo &FalseBBI, ----
1760 unsigned NumDups1, unsigned NumDups2, ----
1761 bool TClobbersPred, bool FClobbersPred, ----
1762 bool RemoveBranch, bool MergeAddEdges) { ----
1763 ----
1764 if (TrueBBI.IsDone || FalseBBI.IsDone || 0
1765 TrueBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1 || FalseBBI.BB->pred_size() > 1) { 0
1766 // Something has changed. It's no longer safe to predicate these blocks. ----
1767 BBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1768 TrueBBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1769 FalseBBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
1770 return false; 0
1771 } ----
1772 ----
1773 if (TrueBBI.BB->hasAddressTaken() || FalseBBI.BB->hasAddressTaken()) 0
1774 // Conservatively abort if-conversion if either BB has its address taken. ----
1775 return false; 0
1776 ----
1777 // Put the predicated instructions from the 'true' block before the ----
1778 // instructions from the 'false' block, unless the true block would clobber ----
1779 // the predicate, in which case, do the opposite. ----
1780 BBInfo *BBI1 = &TrueBBI; 0
1781 BBInfo *BBI2 = &FalseBBI; 0
1782 SmallVector RevCond(BBI.BrCond.begin(), BBI.BrCond.end()); 0
1783 if (TII->reverseBranchCondition(RevCond)) 0
1784 llvm_unreachable("Unable to reverse branch condition!"); 0
1785 SmallVector *Cond1 = &BBI.BrCond; 0
1786 SmallVector *Cond2 = &RevCond; 0
1787 ----
1788 // Figure out the more profitable ordering. ----
1789 bool DoSwap = false; 0
1790 if (TClobbersPred && !FClobbersPred) 0
1791 DoSwap = true; 0
1792 else if (!TClobbersPred && !FClobbersPred) { 0
1793 if (TrueBBI.NonPredSize > FalseBBI.NonPredSize) 0
1794 DoSwap = true; 0
1795 } else if (TClobbersPred && FClobbersPred) 0
1796 llvm_unreachable("Predicate info cannot be clobbered by both sides."); 0
1797 if (DoSwap) { 0
1798 std::swap(BBI1, BBI2); 0
1799 std::swap(Cond1, Cond2); 0
1800 } ----
1801 ----
1802 // Remove the conditional branch from entry to the blocks. ----
1803 BBI.NonPredSize -= TII->removeBranch(*BBI.BB); 0
1804 ----
1805 MachineBasicBlock &MBB1 = *BBI1->BB; 0
1806 MachineBasicBlock &MBB2 = *BBI2->BB; 0
1807 ----
1808 // Initialize the Redefs: ----
1809 // - BB2 live-in regs need implicit uses before being redefined by BB1 ----
1810 // instructions. ----
1811 // - BB1 live-out regs need implicit uses before being redefined by BB2 ----
1812 // instructions. We start with BB1 live-ins so we have the live-out regs ----
1813 // after tracking the BB1 instructions. ----
1814 Redefs.init(*TRI); 0
1815 if (MRI->tracksLiveness()) { 0
1816 Redefs.addLiveInsNoPristines(MBB1); 0
1817 Redefs.addLiveInsNoPristines(MBB2); 0
1818 } ----
1819 ----
1820 // Remove the duplicated instructions at the beginnings of both paths. ----
1821 // Skip dbg_value instructions. ----
1822 MachineBasicBlock::iterator DI1 = MBB1.getFirstNonDebugInstr(false); 0
1823 MachineBasicBlock::iterator DI2 = MBB2.getFirstNonDebugInstr(false); 0
1824 BBI1->NonPredSize -= NumDups1; 0
1825 BBI2->NonPredSize -= NumDups1; 0
1826 ----
1827 // Skip past the dups on each side separately since there may be ----
1828 // differing dbg_value entries. NumDups1 can include a "return" ----
1829 // instruction, if it's not marked as "branch". ----
1830 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumDups1; ++DI1) { 0
1831 if (DI1 == MBB1.end()) 0
1832 break; 0
1833 if (!DI1->isDebugInstr()) 0
1834 ++i; 0
1835 } ----
1836 while (NumDups1 != 0) { 0
1837 // Since this instruction is going to be deleted, update call ----
1838 // site info state if the instruction is call instruction. ----
1839 if (DI2->shouldUpdateCallSiteInfo()) 0
1840 MBB2.getParent()->eraseCallSiteInfo(&*DI2); 0
1841 ----
1842 ++DI2; 0
1843 if (DI2 == MBB2.end()) 0
1844 break; 0
1845 if (!DI2->isDebugInstr()) 0
1846 --NumDups1; 0
1847 } ----
1848 ----
1849 if (MRI->tracksLiveness()) { 0
1850 for (const MachineInstr &MI : make_range(MBB1.begin(), DI1)) { 0
1851 SmallVector, 4> Dummy; 0
1852 Redefs.stepForward(MI, Dummy); 0
1853 } 0
1854 } ----
1855 ----
1856 BBI.BB->splice(BBI.BB->end(), &MBB1, MBB1.begin(), DI1); 0
1857 MBB2.erase(MBB2.begin(), DI2); 0
1858 ----
1859 // The branches have been checked to match, so it is safe to remove the ----
1860 // branch in BB1 and rely on the copy in BB2. The complication is that ----
1861 // the blocks may end with a return instruction, which may or may not ----
1862 // be marked as "branch". If it's not, then it could be included in ----
1863 // "dups1", leaving the blocks potentially empty after moving the common ----
1864 // duplicates. ----
1865 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1866 // Unanalyzable branches must match exactly. Check that now. ----
1867 if (!BBI1->IsBrAnalyzable) 0
1868 verifySameBranchInstructions(&MBB1, &MBB2); 0
1869 #endif ----
1870 // Remove duplicated instructions from the tail of MBB1: any branch ----
1871 // instructions, and the common instructions counted by NumDups2. ----
1872 DI1 = MBB1.end(); 0
1873 while (DI1 != MBB1.begin()) { 0
1874 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Prev = std::prev(DI1); 0
1875 if (!Prev->isBranch() && !Prev->isDebugInstr()) 0
1876 break; 0
1877 DI1 = Prev; 0
1878 } ----
1879 for (unsigned i = 0; i != NumDups2; ) { 0
1880 // NumDups2 only counted non-dbg_value instructions, so this won't ----
1881 // run off the head of the list. ----
1882 assert(DI1 != MBB1.begin()); 0
1883 ----
1884 --DI1; 0
1885 ----
1886 // Since this instruction is going to be deleted, update call ----
1887 // site info state if the instruction is call instruction. ----
1888 if (DI1->shouldUpdateCallSiteInfo()) 0
1889 MBB1.getParent()->eraseCallSiteInfo(&*DI1); 0
1890 ----
1891 // skip dbg_value instructions ----
1892 if (!DI1->isDebugInstr()) 0
1893 ++i; 0
1894 } ----
1895 MBB1.erase(DI1, MBB1.end()); 0
1896 ----
1897 DI2 = BBI2->BB->end(); 0
1898 // The branches have been checked to match. Skip over the branch in the false ----
1899 // block so that we don't try to predicate it. ----
1900 if (RemoveBranch) 0
1901 BBI2->NonPredSize -= TII->removeBranch(*BBI2->BB); 0
1902 else { ----
1903 // Make DI2 point to the end of the range where the common "tail" ----
1904 // instructions could be found. ----
1905 while (DI2 != MBB2.begin()) { 0
1906 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Prev = std::prev(DI2); 0
1907 if (!Prev->isBranch() && !Prev->isDebugInstr()) 0
1908 break; 0
1909 DI2 = Prev; 0
1910 } ----
1911 } ----
1912 while (NumDups2 != 0) { 0
1913 // NumDups2 only counted non-dbg_value instructions, so this won't ----
1914 // run off the head of the list. ----
1915 assert(DI2 != MBB2.begin()); 0
1916 --DI2; 0
1917 // skip dbg_value instructions ----
1918 if (!DI2->isDebugInstr()) 0
1919 --NumDups2; 0
1920 } ----
1921 ----
1922 // Remember which registers would later be defined by the false block. ----
1923 // This allows us not to predicate instructions in the true block that would ----
1924 // later be re-defined. That is, rather than ----
1925 // subeq r0, r1, #1 ----
1926 // addne r0, r1, #1 ----
1927 // generate: ----
1928 // sub r0, r1, #1 ----
1929 // addne r0, r1, #1 ----
1930 SmallSet RedefsByFalse; 0
1931 SmallSet ExtUses; 0
1932 if (TII->isProfitableToUnpredicate(MBB1, MBB2)) { 0
1933 for (const MachineInstr &FI : make_range(MBB2.begin(), DI2)) { 0
1934 if (FI.isDebugInstr()) 0
1935 continue; 0
1936 SmallVector Defs; 0
1937 for (const MachineOperand &MO : FI.operands()) { 0
1938 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1939 continue; 0
1940 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1941 if (!Reg) 0
1942 continue; 0
1943 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
1944 Defs.push_back(Reg); 0
1945 } else if (!RedefsByFalse.count(Reg)) { 0
1946 // These are defined before ctrl flow reach the 'false' instructions. ----
1947 // They cannot be modified by the 'true' instructions. ----
1948 for (MCPhysReg SubReg : TRI->subregs_inclusive(Reg)) 0
1949 ExtUses.insert(SubReg); 0
1950 } ----
1951 } ----
1952 ----
1953 for (MCPhysReg Reg : Defs) { 0
1954 if (!ExtUses.count(Reg)) { 0
1955 for (MCPhysReg SubReg : TRI->subregs_inclusive(Reg)) 0
1956 RedefsByFalse.insert(SubReg); 0
1957 } ----
1958 } ----
1959 } 0
1960 } ----
1961 ----
1962 // Predicate the 'true' block. ----
1963 PredicateBlock(*BBI1, MBB1.end(), *Cond1, &RedefsByFalse); 0
1964 ----
1965 // After predicating BBI1, if there is a predicated terminator in BBI1 and ----
1966 // a non-predicated in BBI2, then we don't want to predicate the one from ----
1967 // BBI2. The reason is that if we merged these blocks, we would end up with ----
1968 // two predicated terminators in the same block. ----
1969 // Also, if the branches in MBB1 and MBB2 were non-analyzable, then don't ----
1970 // predicate them either. They were checked to be identical, and so the ----
1971 // same branch would happen regardless of which path was taken. ----
1972 if (!MBB2.empty() && (DI2 == MBB2.end())) { 0
1973 MachineBasicBlock::iterator BBI1T = MBB1.getFirstTerminator(); 0
1974 MachineBasicBlock::iterator BBI2T = MBB2.getFirstTerminator(); 0
1975 bool BB1Predicated = BBI1T != MBB1.end() && TII->isPredicated(*BBI1T); 0
1976 bool BB2NonPredicated = BBI2T != MBB2.end() && !TII->isPredicated(*BBI2T); 0
1977 if (BB2NonPredicated && (BB1Predicated || !BBI2->IsBrAnalyzable)) 0
1978 --DI2; 0
1979 } ----
1980 ----
1981 // Predicate the 'false' block. ----
1982 PredicateBlock(*BBI2, DI2, *Cond2); 0
1983 ----
1984 // Merge the true block into the entry of the diamond. ----
1985 MergeBlocks(BBI, *BBI1, MergeAddEdges); 0
1986 MergeBlocks(BBI, *BBI2, MergeAddEdges); 0
1987 return true; 0
1988 } 0
1989 ----
1990 /// If convert an almost-diamond sub-CFG where the true ----
1991 /// and false blocks share a common tail. ----
1992 bool IfConverter::IfConvertForkedDiamond( 0
1993 BBInfo &BBI, IfcvtKind Kind, ----
1994 unsigned NumDups1, unsigned NumDups2, ----
1995 bool TClobbersPred, bool FClobbersPred) { ----
1996 BBInfo &TrueBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.TrueBB->getNumber()]; 0
1997 BBInfo &FalseBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.FalseBB->getNumber()]; 0
1998 ----
1999 // Save the debug location for later. ----
2000 DebugLoc dl; 0
2001 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TIE = TrueBBI.BB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
2002 if (TIE != TrueBBI.BB->end()) 0
2003 dl = TIE->getDebugLoc(); 0
2004 // Removing branches from both blocks is safe, because we have already ----
2005 // determined that both blocks have the same branch instructions. The branch ----
2006 // will be added back at the end, unpredicated. ----
2007 if (!IfConvertDiamondCommon( 0
2008 BBI, TrueBBI, FalseBBI, ----
2009 NumDups1, NumDups2, ----
2010 TClobbersPred, FClobbersPred, ----
2011 /* RemoveBranch */ true, /* MergeAddEdges */ true)) ----
2012 return false; 0
2013 ----
2014 // Add back the branch. ----
2015 // Debug location saved above when removing the branch from BBI2 ----
2016 TII->insertBranch(*BBI.BB, TrueBBI.TrueBB, TrueBBI.FalseBB, 0
2017 TrueBBI.BrCond, dl); ----
2018 ----
2019 // Update block info. ----
2020 BBI.IsDone = TrueBBI.IsDone = FalseBBI.IsDone = true; 0
2021 InvalidatePreds(*BBI.BB); 0
2022 ----
2023 // FIXME: Must maintain LiveIns. ----
2024 return true; 0
2025 } 0
2026 ----
2027 /// If convert a diamond sub-CFG. ----
2028 bool IfConverter::IfConvertDiamond(BBInfo &BBI, IfcvtKind Kind, 0
2029 unsigned NumDups1, unsigned NumDups2, ----
2030 bool TClobbersPred, bool FClobbersPred) { ----
2031 BBInfo &TrueBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.TrueBB->getNumber()]; 0
2032 BBInfo &FalseBBI = BBAnalysis[BBI.FalseBB->getNumber()]; 0
2033 MachineBasicBlock *TailBB = TrueBBI.TrueBB; 0
2034 ----
2035 // True block must fall through or end with an unanalyzable terminator. ----
2036 if (!TailBB) { 0
2037 if (blockAlwaysFallThrough(TrueBBI)) 0
2038 TailBB = FalseBBI.TrueBB; 0
2039 assert((TailBB || !TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable) && "Unexpected!"); 0
2040 } ----
2041 ----
2042 if (!IfConvertDiamondCommon( 0
2043 BBI, TrueBBI, FalseBBI, ----
2044 NumDups1, NumDups2, ----
2045 TClobbersPred, FClobbersPred, ----
2046 /* RemoveBranch */ TrueBBI.IsBrAnalyzable, 0
2047 /* MergeAddEdges */ TailBB == nullptr)) ----
2048 return false; 0
2049 ----
2050 // If the if-converted block falls through or unconditionally branches into ----
2051 // the tail block, and the tail block does not have other predecessors, then ----
2052 // fold the tail block in as well. Otherwise, unless it falls through to the ----
2053 // tail, add a unconditional branch to it. ----
2054 if (TailBB) { 0
2055 // We need to remove the edges to the true and false blocks manually since ----
2056 // we didn't let IfConvertDiamondCommon update the CFG. ----
2057 BBI.BB->removeSuccessor(TrueBBI.BB); 0
2058 BBI.BB->removeSuccessor(FalseBBI.BB, true); 0
2059 ----
2060 BBInfo &TailBBI = BBAnalysis[TailBB->getNumber()]; 0
2061 bool CanMergeTail = !TailBBI.HasFallThrough && 0
2062 !TailBBI.BB->hasAddressTaken(); 0
2063 // The if-converted block can still have a predicated terminator ----
2064 // (e.g. a predicated return). If that is the case, we cannot merge ----
2065 // it with the tail block. ----
2066 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator TI = BBI.BB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
2067 if (TI != BBI.BB->end() && TII->isPredicated(*TI)) 0
2068 CanMergeTail = false; 0
2069 // There may still be a fall-through edge from BBI1 or BBI2 to TailBB; ----
2070 // check if there are any other predecessors besides those. ----
2071 unsigned NumPreds = TailBB->pred_size(); 0
2072 if (NumPreds > 1) 0
2073 CanMergeTail = false; 0
2074 else if (NumPreds == 1 && CanMergeTail) { 0
2075 MachineBasicBlock::pred_iterator PI = TailBB->pred_begin(); 0
2076 if (*PI != TrueBBI.BB && *PI != FalseBBI.BB) 0
2077 CanMergeTail = false; 0
2078 } ----
2079 if (CanMergeTail) { 0
2080 MergeBlocks(BBI, TailBBI); 0
2081 TailBBI.IsDone = true; 0
2082 } else { ----
2083 BBI.BB->addSuccessor(TailBB, BranchProbability::getOne()); 0
2084 InsertUncondBranch(*BBI.BB, *TailBB, TII); 0
2085 BBI.HasFallThrough = false; 0
2086 } ----
2087 } ----
2088 ----
2089 // Update block info. ----
2090 BBI.IsDone = TrueBBI.IsDone = FalseBBI.IsDone = true; 0
2091 InvalidatePreds(*BBI.BB); 0
2092 ----
2093 // FIXME: Must maintain LiveIns. ----
2094 return true; 0
2095 } ----
2096 ----
2097 static bool MaySpeculate(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
2098 SmallSet &LaterRedefs) { ----
2099 bool SawStore = true; 0
2100 if (!MI.isSafeToMove(nullptr, SawStore)) 0
2101 return false; 0
2102 ----
2103 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
2104 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
2105 continue; 0
2106 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
2107 if (!Reg) 0
2108 continue; 0
2109 if (MO.isDef() && !LaterRedefs.count(Reg)) 0
2110 return false; 0
2111 } ----
2112 ----
2113 return true; 0
2114 } ----
2115 ----
2116 /// Predicate instructions from the start of the block to the specified end with ----
2117 /// the specified condition. ----
2118 void IfConverter::PredicateBlock(BBInfo &BBI, 0
2119 MachineBasicBlock::iterator E, ----
2120 SmallVectorImpl &Cond, ----
2121 SmallSet *LaterRedefs) { ----
2122 bool AnyUnpred = false; 0
2123 bool MaySpec = LaterRedefs != nullptr; 0
2124 for (MachineInstr &I : make_range(BBI.BB->begin(), E)) { 0
2125 if (I.isDebugInstr() || TII->isPredicated(I)) 0
2126 continue; 0
2127 // It may be possible not to predicate an instruction if it's the 'true' ----
2128 // side of a diamond and the 'false' side may re-define the instruction's ----
2129 // defs. ----
2130 if (MaySpec && MaySpeculate(I, *LaterRedefs)) { 0
2131 AnyUnpred = true; 0
2132 continue; 0
2133 } ----
2134 // If any instruction is predicated, then every instruction after it must ----
2135 // be predicated. ----
2136 MaySpec = false; 0
2137 if (!TII->PredicateInstruction(I, Cond)) { 0
2138 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2139 dbgs() << "Unable to predicate " << I << "!\n"; 0
2140 #endif ----
2141 llvm_unreachable(nullptr); 0
2142 } ----
2143 ----
2144 // If the predicated instruction now redefines a register as the result of ----
2145 // if-conversion, add an implicit kill. ----
2146 UpdatePredRedefs(I, Redefs); 0
2147 } ----
2148 ----
2149 BBI.Predicate.append(Cond.begin(), Cond.end()); 0
2150 ----
2151 BBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
2152 BBI.NonPredSize = 0; 0
2153 ----
2154 ++NumIfConvBBs; 0
2155 if (AnyUnpred) 0
2156 ++NumUnpred; 0
2157 } 0
2158 ----
2159 /// Copy and predicate instructions from source BB to the destination block. ----
2160 /// Skip end of block branches if IgnoreBr is true. ----
2161 void IfConverter::CopyAndPredicateBlock(BBInfo &ToBBI, BBInfo &FromBBI, 0
2162 SmallVectorImpl &Cond, ----
2163 bool IgnoreBr) { ----
2164 MachineFunction &MF = *ToBBI.BB->getParent(); 0
2165 ----
2166 MachineBasicBlock &FromMBB = *FromBBI.BB; 0
2167 for (MachineInstr &I : FromMBB) { 0
2168 // Do not copy the end of the block branches. ----
2169 if (IgnoreBr && I.isBranch()) 0
2170 break; 0
2171 ----
2172 MachineInstr *MI = MF.CloneMachineInstr(&I); 0
2173 // Make a copy of the call site info. ----
2174 if (I.isCandidateForCallSiteEntry()) 0
2175 MF.copyCallSiteInfo(&I, MI); 0
2176 ----
2177 ToBBI.BB->insert(ToBBI.BB->end(), MI); 0
2178 ToBBI.NonPredSize++; 0
2179 unsigned ExtraPredCost = TII->getPredicationCost(I); 0
2180 unsigned NumCycles = SchedModel.computeInstrLatency(&I, false); 0
2181 if (NumCycles > 1) 0
2182 ToBBI.ExtraCost += NumCycles-1; 0
2183 ToBBI.ExtraCost2 += ExtraPredCost; 0
2184 ----
2185 if (!TII->isPredicated(I) && !MI->isDebugInstr()) { 0
2186 if (!TII->PredicateInstruction(*MI, Cond)) { 0
2187 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
2188 dbgs() << "Unable to predicate " << I << "!\n"; 0
2189 #endif ----
2190 llvm_unreachable(nullptr); 0
2191 } ----
2192 } ----
2193 ----
2194 // If the predicated instruction now redefines a register as the result of ----
2195 // if-conversion, add an implicit kill. ----
2196 UpdatePredRedefs(*MI, Redefs); 0
2197 } ----
2198 ----
2199 if (!IgnoreBr) { 0
2200 std::vector Succs(FromMBB.succ_begin(), ----
2201 FromMBB.succ_end()); 0
2202 MachineBasicBlock *NBB = getNextBlock(FromMBB); 0
2203 MachineBasicBlock *FallThrough = FromBBI.HasFallThrough ? NBB : nullptr; 0
2204 ----
2205 for (MachineBasicBlock *Succ : Succs) { 0
2206 // Fallthrough edge can't be transferred. ----
2207 if (Succ == FallThrough) 0
2208 continue; 0
2209 ToBBI.BB->addSuccessor(Succ); 0
2210 } ----
2211 } 0
2212 ----
2213 ToBBI.Predicate.append(FromBBI.Predicate.begin(), FromBBI.Predicate.end()); 0
2214 ToBBI.Predicate.append(Cond.begin(), Cond.end()); 0
2215 ----
2216 ToBBI.ClobbersPred |= FromBBI.ClobbersPred; 0
2217 ToBBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
2218 ----
2219 ++NumDupBBs; 0
2220 } 0
2221 ----
2222 /// Move all instructions from FromBB to the end of ToBB. This will leave ----
2223 /// FromBB as an empty block, so remove all of its successor edges and move it ----
2224 /// to the end of the function. If AddEdges is true, i.e., when FromBBI's ----
2225 /// branch is being moved, add those successor edges to ToBBI and remove the old ----
2226 /// edge from ToBBI to FromBBI. ----
2227 void IfConverter::MergeBlocks(BBInfo &ToBBI, BBInfo &FromBBI, bool AddEdges) { 0
2228 MachineBasicBlock &FromMBB = *FromBBI.BB; 0
2229 assert(!FromMBB.hasAddressTaken() && 0
2230 "Removing a BB whose address is taken!"); ----
2231 ----
2232 // If we're about to splice an INLINEASM_BR from FromBBI, we need to update ----
2233 // ToBBI's successor list accordingly. ----
2234 if (FromMBB.mayHaveInlineAsmBr()) 0
2235 for (MachineInstr &MI : FromMBB) 0
2236 if (MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::INLINEASM_BR) 0
2237 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) 0
2238 if (MO.isMBB() && !ToBBI.BB->isSuccessor(MO.getMBB())) 0
2239 ToBBI.BB->addSuccessor(MO.getMBB(), BranchProbability::getZero()); 0
2240 ----
2241 // In case FromMBB contains terminators (e.g. return instruction), ----
2242 // first move the non-terminator instructions, then the terminators. ----
2243 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FromTI = FromMBB.getFirstTerminator(); 0

2245 ToBBI.BB->splice(ToTI, &FromMBB, FromMBB.begin(), FromTI); 0
2246 ----
2247 // If FromBB has non-predicated terminator we should copy it at the end. ----
2248 if (FromTI != FromMBB.end() && !TII->isPredicated(*FromTI)) 0
2249 ToTI = ToBBI.BB->end(); 0
2250 ToBBI.BB->splice(ToTI, &FromMBB, FromTI, FromMBB.end()); 0
2251 ----
2252 // Force normalizing the successors' probabilities of ToBBI.BB to convert all ----
2253 // unknown probabilities into known ones. ----
2254 // FIXME: This usage is too tricky and in the future we would like to ----
2255 // eliminate all unknown probabilities in MBB. ----
2256 if (ToBBI.IsBrAnalyzable) 0
2257 ToBBI.BB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
2258 ----
2259 SmallVector FromSuccs(FromMBB.successors()); 0
2260 MachineBasicBlock *NBB = getNextBlock(FromMBB); 0
2261 MachineBasicBlock *FallThrough = FromBBI.HasFallThrough ? NBB : nullptr; 0
2262 // The edge probability from ToBBI.BB to FromMBB, which is only needed when ----
2263 // AddEdges is true and FromMBB is a successor of ToBBI.BB. ----
2264 auto To2FromProb = BranchProbability::getZero(); 0
2265 if (AddEdges && ToBBI.BB->isSuccessor(&FromMBB)) { 0
2266 // Remove the old edge but remember the edge probability so we can calculate ----
2267 // the correct weights on the new edges being added further down. ----
2268 To2FromProb = MBPI->getEdgeProbability(ToBBI.BB, &FromMBB); 0
2269 ToBBI.BB->removeSuccessor(&FromMBB); 0
2270 } ----
2271 ----
2272 for (MachineBasicBlock *Succ : FromSuccs) { 0
2273 // Fallthrough edge can't be transferred. ----
2274 if (Succ == FallThrough) { 0
2275 FromMBB.removeSuccessor(Succ); 0
2276 continue; 0
2277 } ----
2278 ----
2279 auto NewProb = BranchProbability::getZero(); 0
2280 if (AddEdges) { 0
2281 // Calculate the edge probability for the edge from ToBBI.BB to Succ, ----
2282 // which is a portion of the edge probability from FromMBB to Succ. The ----
2283 // portion ratio is the edge probability from ToBBI.BB to FromMBB (if ----
2284 // FromBBI is a successor of ToBBI.BB. See comment below for exception). ----
2285 NewProb = MBPI->getEdgeProbability(&FromMBB, Succ); 0
2286 ----
2287 // To2FromProb is 0 when FromMBB is not a successor of ToBBI.BB. This ----
2288 // only happens when if-converting a diamond CFG and FromMBB is the ----
2289 // tail BB. In this case FromMBB post-dominates ToBBI.BB and hence we ----
2290 // could just use the probabilities on FromMBB's out-edges when adding ----
2291 // new successors. ----
2292 if (!To2FromProb.isZero()) 0
2293 NewProb *= To2FromProb; 0
2294 } ----
2295 ----
2296 FromMBB.removeSuccessor(Succ); 0
2297 ----
2298 if (AddEdges) { 0
2299 // If the edge from ToBBI.BB to Succ already exists, update the ----
2300 // probability of this edge by adding NewProb to it. An example is shown ----
2301 // below, in which A is ToBBI.BB and B is FromMBB. In this case we ----
2302 // don't have to set C as A's successor as it already is. We only need to ----
2303 // update the edge probability on A->C. Note that B will not be ----
2304 // immediately removed from A's successors. It is possible that B->D is ----
2305 // not removed either if D is a fallthrough of B. Later the edge A->D ----
2306 // (generated here) and B->D will be combined into one edge. To maintain ----
2307 // correct edge probability of this combined edge, we need to set the edge ----
2308 // probability of A->B to zero, which is already done above. The edge ----
2309 // probability on A->D is calculated by scaling the original probability ----
2310 // on A->B by the probability of B->D. ----
2311 // ----
2312 // Before ifcvt: After ifcvt (assume B->D is kept): ----
2313 // ----
2314 // A A ----
2315 // /| /|\ ----
2316 // / B / B| ----
2317 // | /| | || ----
2318 // |/ | | |/ ----
2319 // C D C D ----
2320 // ----
2321 if (ToBBI.BB->isSuccessor(Succ)) 0
2322 ToBBI.BB->setSuccProbability( 0
2323 find(ToBBI.BB->successors(), Succ), 0
2324 MBPI->getEdgeProbability(ToBBI.BB, Succ) + NewProb); 0
2325 else ----
2326 ToBBI.BB->addSuccessor(Succ, NewProb); 0
2327 } ----
2328 } ----
2329 ----
2330 // Move the now empty FromMBB out of the way to the end of the function so ----
2331 // it doesn't interfere with fallthrough checks done by canFallThroughTo(). ----
2332 MachineBasicBlock *Last = &*FromMBB.getParent()->rbegin(); 0
2333 if (Last != &FromMBB) 0
2334 FromMBB.moveAfter(Last); 0
2335 ----
2336 // Normalize the probabilities of ToBBI.BB's successors with all adjustment ----
2337 // we've done above. ----
2338 if (ToBBI.IsBrAnalyzable && FromBBI.IsBrAnalyzable) 0
2339 ToBBI.BB->normalizeSuccProbs(); 0
2340 ----
2341 ToBBI.Predicate.append(FromBBI.Predicate.begin(), FromBBI.Predicate.end()); 0
2342 FromBBI.Predicate.clear(); 0
2343 ----
2344 ToBBI.NonPredSize += FromBBI.NonPredSize; 0
2345 ToBBI.ExtraCost += FromBBI.ExtraCost; 0
2346 ToBBI.ExtraCost2 += FromBBI.ExtraCost2; 0
2347 FromBBI.NonPredSize = 0; 0
2348 FromBBI.ExtraCost = 0; 0
2349 FromBBI.ExtraCost2 = 0; 0
2350 ----
2351 ToBBI.ClobbersPred |= FromBBI.ClobbersPred; 0
2352 ToBBI.HasFallThrough = FromBBI.HasFallThrough; 0
2353 ToBBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
2354 FromBBI.IsAnalyzed = false; 0
2355 } 0

2359 return new IfConverter(std::move(Ftor)); 0
